title: "seafood in the pink"
directions: In a pot, cover bottom with olive oil.
Season with salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Heat and quickly cook chopped garlic (2 tablespoons), making sure the garlic does not brown.
Add marinara sauce and wine.
Simmer on low heat for at least 1/2 hour.

title: harriett's congealed salad
directions: Make Jell-O with 2 cups hot water. Let Jell-O cool. Put cream cheese in blender. Add 1 cup heated pineapple juice over cream cheese. Blend well. Mix with cool Jell-O. Add crushed pineapple, celery, carrots, pecans and Cool Whip. Pour into 13 x 9-inch oblong Pyrex dish. Put in the refrigerator to set. Best if left to set overnight.

title: baked grilled potatoes
directions: Keep the skins of potatoes and cut as you would for fried potatoes.
Cut onions and peppers; add to the potatoes.
Pour Italian salad dressing and oleo over potatoes, peppers and onions. Wrap in heavy aluminum foil.
Cook on barbecue grill for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: no bake peanut butter logs
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Mix; use hands, if necessary.
Shape into small logs.
Chill and then frost.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour or until wooden pick comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on a wire rack. Yields 1 loaf.

title: new orleans style beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper of choice.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Cover with water.
Mix and cook in a slow cooker on medium overnight.
Be sure you have enough water to keep the beans from boiling dry and burning.
Serve over rice.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips.
Mix chips and noodles together.
Drop teaspoon of mixture onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: herbed toast
directions: About 20 minutes before serving or early in day:
With knife, cut off crusts from bread slices.
(Reserve crusts for making bread crumbs for another day.)
Arrange bread slices on cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In small saucepan over medium heat, heat butter or margarine, savory and fennel seed until butter melts.
Brush bread slices with butter mixture; bake 15 minutes or until golden on both sides, turning bread slices once. Makes 8 servings.

title: noel chicken a la paris
directions: Place chicken in pan skin side up.
Combine rest of ingredients including liquid from mushrooms.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serve with rice/wild rice.

title: cranberry icebox cookies
directions: Shape in roll; chill 3 hours.

title: mom brown's barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Pour off fat, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble. Drain off all the grease, except one tablespoon.
Add onion and saute until golden brown.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Stir into onion mixture until blended.
Add clam juice.
Stir until smooth.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread in small pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix ingredients; shape into cakes and fry quickly until brown.

title: quick cake
directions: Break egg whites into cup; add shortening to half fill the cup.
Then add milk to completely fill the cup.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add in egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice or frost
as desired.

title: rice broccoli
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil.
Melt cheese in soup and milk mixture.
Add broccoli, etc. to soup.
Mix in rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in uncovered buttered casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mint cut-outs
directions: Mix 3 1/2 cups confectioners sugar, milk, flavor and color. Mix in enough confectioners sugar to make a smooth dough.
Roll 1/4-inch thick between wax paper.
Cut in shapes and place on wax paper, uncovered, 1 to 2 hours.
Turn over and let stand 1 hour. Decorate as desired.

title: hearty hodgepodge stew
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat, onion and garlic until tender. Stir in minestrone soup, pork and beans, 3 cups water, celery, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not add salt and pepper!
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: veggie burgers
directions: In a well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, place layers of well drained, thinly sliced raw potatoes.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Finely cut pimiento strips and green onion tops.
Pour small amount of Cream Sauce over them and sprinkle with grated American cheese, using about 1/2 cup altogether.
Repeat until casserole is filled.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and continue baking for 1 more hour or until potatoes are tender.
Keep casserole covered for the first hour, then uncover.
Serves 8.

title: baked chicken and rice supreme
directions: In a saucepan, heat soups, milk and margarine.
Add rices and seasoning packet.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 400°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add both cans of corn and milk.
Mix well.

title: ziti charcoal burners style(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain off drippings. Return 2 tablespoons to the pan.
Saute onion in drippings until just transparent.
Add wine and cook until wine is reduced by half.
Cook pasta and drain well; return to pot.
Add bacon, onion mixture, eggs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly until pasta is well coated.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: About 3 hours before serving time, mix together the rice, soup and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, over the rice.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Bake in slow oven for 3 hours.
Turn chicken pieces over after 1 1/2 hours of baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook onion in butter until tender. Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole pan.
Put corn chips and cheese on top.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cut crust from bread and cut into quarters.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place alternately bread and cheese (2 layers each). Pour melted margarine over cheese and bread.
Beat eggs until light.
Add salt, half and half and mustard.
Pour mixture over bread and cheese.
Cover and let set in refrigerator overnight. Before baking, sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli mushroom quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with egg white and refrigerate.
Spread cheese in pie shell.
In the butter, saute onion until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Add broccoli, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Remove from heat and pour in pie shell.
Beat eggs; add half and half and nutmeg.
Pour over vegetables and cheese in shell.
Bake at 375° about 40 to 50 minutes, until golden brown and puffed.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Cook bouillon cubes, water, onions and celery 20 minutes in covered heavy pan.
Add potatoes, frozen broccoli and soup and cook 30 minutes, covered.
Add cheese and heat until melted.

title: congealed apricot salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add apricot gelatin. Mix and add cream cheese. Stir until dissolved. Add the ice water to cool the mixture. Add celery and nuts.
When starting to gel, fold in whipped topping and congeal in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into 2-inch squares when congealed and serve on lettuce.

title: syrian bread
directions: Measure warm water in a bowl.
Crumble in yeast; stir to dissolve.
Add salt, sugar and oil.
Stir in 1/2 flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place dough, smooth side down, in a greased bowl.
Turn to grease all sides.
Cover; let rise 45 minutes.
Press down and let rise 15 more minutes.
Divide in 4 parts.
Flatten with knuckles.
Let rise 20 or 30 minutes.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Bring to boil, simmer 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine cottage cheese and egg. In a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan, place 2 medium zucchini, sliced crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons flour. Top with cheese mixture and half the meat mixture.
Place 2 more zucchini sliced the same on top of this, sprinkled with another 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and then remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for around 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with additional cheese. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: rhubarb jello bars
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat combine rhubarb, sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and dry jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Set aside to cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, margarine and sugar; mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder and fold in.
Mix in blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 12.

title: rhonda's lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain.
Add Ragu to beef and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Pour French dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill for 2 hours. Add onion, celery and salt.
Add mayonnaise and mix.
Chill 4 hours.

title: party rye
directions: Mix all ingredients, then spread on slices of the party rye bread.
Broil until bubbly.

title: pizza spins
directions: Crumble ground turkey and sausage in microwave casserole dish (1/2 to 2 quart dish).
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir and microwave another 4 minutes.
Drain all grease. Crumble cooked meat and add Velveeta cheese (cubed).
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Add Italian seasoning and stir until all ingredients are mixed well.
Spoon onto cocktail rye and bake in oven for 4 to 5 minutes at 350° on cookie sheet. Remove to serving platter with spatula, for all guests to enjoy.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine the cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Then mix together the remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan or can be put in a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar
together.
Let cool.
Add orange juice and fruit.
Freeze.
Set out an hour before serving.

title: fresh flower formula
directions: Keep flower stems in 3 to 4-inches of water.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Drain and mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients, except avocados and let set for about 4 hours. Add avocados just before serving. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: brenda's pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in large oven bag and place in pan.
Add tomatoes, soup mix and pepper.
Blend in bag by squeezing.
Trim fat off roast; put roast in bag.
Turn bag to coat roast with sauce.
Put vegetables in around roast.
Close bag; ventilate.
Bake until roast is done, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: pizza fondue
directions: In saucepan, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Add cheeses gradually; stir over low heat until cheeses are melted.
Blend together cornstarch and wine; add to cheese mixture.
Pour into fondue pot.
Spear bread cube with fondue fork; dip in mixture, swirling to coat.

title: hot dog creole
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in salt, sugar, tomatoes and catsup; simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slice hot dogs into small disks. Add hot dogs to pan and simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Knead together and roll into balls. Melt 1 (12 ounce) package semi-sweet chocolate chips and 1/2 bar paraffin. Put each ball on a toothpick to dip into melted chocolate mixture. Put on wax paper to cool.

title: sherbet christmas pie
directions: Place lime sherbet in bowl.
Stir in 1/4 Cool Whip until smooth*.
Spoon into crust.
Place raspberry sherbet in bowl.
Stir in 1/4 Cool Whip until smooth*.
Spoon on top of lime sherbet/Cool Whip mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Let stand about 10 minutes before serving. Garnish with Christmas candy.
Store pie in freezer.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding together.
Add Cool Whip, crushed pineapple (undrained) and marshmallows.
Mix well, then refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain noodles well.
Place in hot casserole or deep platter over low heat.
Add, a little at a time, the butter, cheese and the cream, which has been slightly beaten.
Toss gently after each addition.
Season with pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and Crisco with hands until it looks like Bisquick.
Add milk and yeast mixture.
Mix.
Place in a mixing bowl, cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Roll out on a floured surface and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place on a cookie sheet and brush top with buttermilk.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown.

title: mince pie
directions: In tin pie pan, place home made pie crust.
Cover with mince meat.
Do not make it thick, make very thin layer.
Cover mince meat with sugar and butter.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken pieces in pan (you can omit this step if in a hurry).
Put in crock-pot and add previous mixture.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours on low.
Serve with rice.

title: apple crumb coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and sour cream. Mix well 2 minutes. Fold in apples. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed well with nonstick spray. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Sprinkle half over the batter; swirl. Add rest of cake mixture, then sprinkle the brown sugar mixture on top; swirl again. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick stuck in middle of cake comes out clean.

title: more
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain off grease. Mix in spaghetti sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper and corn.
Cook potatoes according to box directions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew squash with onion.
Cover bottom of buttered dish and sides with toasted bread crumbs.
Layer squash.
Layer cheese and eggs.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Layer cheese, eggs and squash until all is used up.
Pour soup over top and then squash juice.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar artichokes into a small frypan. Drain the other jar.
Chop artichokes fine, discarding any hard pieces; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to marinade and saute until limp.
Drain off excess marinade.

title: mammaw's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar and put in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Arrange pineapple slices, cherries and nuts on top. Mix cake mix per directions on box.
Pour in cake pan on top of pineapple, etc., filling pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let stand in pan for 5 minutes, then turn onto plate. Best served warm with whipped topping.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place onion slices on top; add mixed vegetables.
Next put Tater Tots on top.
Mix water with mushroom soup and spoon on top of casserole, spreading evenly.
Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.
Serves 6 people.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In large bowl, combine applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and beat well.
Pour in greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lazy man cherry cobbler
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt the butter in the baking pan as the oven preheats.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Blend with the milk.
Pour this batter over the melted butter.
Put in the fruit.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes during which time the batter will rise and the fruit sink.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream or without any topping at all.

title: scotchies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening; beat in sugar slowly.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture, then the oats, pecans and coconut. Drop from a teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Flatten to 1/8-inch thick with bottom of a glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
(I always used to bake 2 or 3 batches at once.
My family could really make them disappear!)

title: strawberry jam
directions: Boil the first 2 ingredients 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add 3 more cups sugar.
Boil 5 more minutes. Stir constantly.
Put in jars and let set until morning. Seal or freeze.

title: low calorie italian dressing
directions: Into small bowl or covered jar, measure all ingredients; stir with fork or cover and shake until well blended.
Cover; keep refrigerated.
Stir before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Per tablespoon: 5 calories and 5 mg sodium.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions and set aside. Cook broccoli until thawed only. Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Mix rice, onion, celery and cream of mushroom soup in casserole. Add broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fast and easy spinach lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach and oregano.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1 heaping cup of sauce, then 3 uncooked lasagne noodles, side by side. Spread 1/2 cheese and spinach mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with 3 remaining lasagne noodles and 1 cup sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cup of cheese over top.
Pour 3/4 cup of water around edges of pan. Cover lightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand additional 15 minutes with foil before serving.
If made ahead, add water just before baking.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in large Pyrex casserole. Place cut-up chicken over rice mixture.
Sprinkle second 1/2 package of onion soup mix over chicken.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake additional 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: First day take cranberries and sugar and mix.
Store in refrigerator over night.
Second day add crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Third day add a cup of Cool Whip.
Ready to eat the fourth day.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Place marshmallows in a large bowl and mix thoroughly with pineapple.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Fold cream in just before serving.
Serve in dessert dishes.
Garnish with nuts or maraschino cherries or serve plain.

title: lemon pasta primavera
directions: 1. Fill large saucepan 1/2 full of water.
Cover and bring to a boil on high heat for pasta.

title: perfect bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs; pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in 8-inch round baking dish. Place in shallow pan on oven rack; pour hot water around it, 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from pot and cool.
Save broth.

title: strawberry custard ice cream
directions: In saucepan, combine eggs, milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Allow to cool. Blend in cream.
Fold in berries.
Pour into your ice cream freezer container and freeze according to freezer directions.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch skillet and place in oven to heat.
Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour batter into prepared skillet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
This cornbread is very moist.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes with mixer or by hand.
When all lumps are removed, add cream cheese in small pieces and then the butter. Beat well until cheese and butter are both melted and completely mixed.
Mix in sour cream.

title: baked bass supreme
directions: Lay fish on foil; add lemon, onion, pepper and seasonings. Fold foil.
Bake at 450° for 13 to 20 minutes.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix together well. Chill and serve with chips.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Make cake-like brownies according to package.
Place marshmallows, sticky side down, on top of brownies while still hot.
Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Pour this over marshmallows to make an icing.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and oil.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Put out on floured board and knead until dough is not sticky.
Put in large greased bowl and cover with Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove and let rest on floured board for 15 minutes.
Make out into rolls or loaves and let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: quick peach crumble
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water.
Peel and slice peaches.
Add to syrup and simmer until peaches are heated (or heat canned peaches in saucepan).
Crush sugar cookies into crumbs.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Add and stir in cookie crumbs and walnuts.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.
To serve, place warm peaches in small compotes; spoon a little
juice over; sprinkle with about 2 tablespoons crumb mixture.
Serve with cream or soft vanilla ice cream.
Top with more crumb mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Do in oven at 350.
As it melts, stir.

title: taco bake
directions: Tear tortillas in 1/2.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Be sure all of bottom is covered. Spread beans on shells (warm beans in microwave to spread easier).
Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning as directed on package.
Layer on beans and top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or microwave until all warm and cheese is melted.
Serve with chopped lettuce and tomatoes.

title: hash brown and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, drain and set aside.
In saucepan on stove or in microwave, melt butter.
Add Velveeta, stirring frequently to prevent sticking.
Add soup and sour cream.
Add cooked sausage. Place frozen hash browns in large oblong pan.
Pour cheese and soup mixture over hash browns.
(Casserole may be baked at this point or place in the refrigerator and baked the next morning.)
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Sprinkle croutons on top and bake until brown.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter with egg yolks; add rind, lemon juice and flour.
Mix; add milk and beat egg whites.
Fold in mixture. Bake 45 minutes in slow oven, 325° to 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat and drain off fat.
Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water.
Cover.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add sugar; continue mixing at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour and frosting mix; add pecans until well blended. Pour batter into well-greased and floured pan (Bundt).
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours before removing from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Melt margarine; add cracker crumbs.
Pat into 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch glass dish.
Chill.
Cream the cream cheese and add milk and sugar.
Spread on cracker crust.
Pour pie filling on top. Chill.

title: peach pie
directions: Put peaches and syrup in large Pyrex dish.
Mix sugar and margarine well.
Add flour, eggs and vanilla.
Spoon mixture on top of peaches.
Cook 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: apple muffins
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Add apples and dry ingredients; mix well.
Fill muffin tins half full.

title: cheese pie(appetizer)
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine egg, flour, salt, pepper and half of milk; beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk; beat until well blended.
Stir in one-half of the cheese.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter and shortening in 1-quart saucepan over low heat. Cool 15 minutes.

title: potluck vegetable casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spread butter and bread crumbs on top. Place in greased 15 or 17 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: arlea's chicken
directions: Roll chicken in mixture of flour, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken for 10 minutes on each side.
Place browned chicken in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix soup and milk in a bowl; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown and drain ground round.
Saute onion; add to meat.
Add Worcestershire sauce (approximately 2 tablespoons).
Add salt and pepper; mix well.
Press mixture into bottom of baking dish.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into bowl. Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes. Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: there's-no-easier roast beef
directions: Pour half of barbecue sauce into bottom of slow cooker. Add roast. Top with remaining barbecue sauce. Cover. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Slice roast and serve with sauce.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
In a large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, sugar and yeast/water mixture.
Stir in remaining flour until you have a smooth dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Beat with electric beater.
Add Cool Whip and mix good, using a spoon.
Add your fruit and stir. Chill several hours.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix all ingredients in crock pot on high for 1 hour.
Keep warm on low.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add soda that has been dissolved in coffee; let cool.
Add beaten egg, salt, ginger and vanilla. Add molasses and enough flour to roll.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out; put on cookie sheet.
Top with sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Drain off any liquid from hot potatoes.
Rice potatoes while hot into a bowl.
Add milk mixed with egg yolks and cheese, salt, onion and parsley.
Whip until fluffy.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into the potato mixture.
Pile lightly into 8 mounds on a greased cookie sheet or shallow pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Serve immediately while still puffy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt in double boiler and serve.

title: creamed soups
directions: Cook fresh vegetable in broth and onion.
Process or blend. Make roux with the oil and margarine, cooking for a minute to eliminate the raw flour taste.
Add milk and cook until thick. Add vegetable puree.
Makes 3 cups, 170 calories per cup, 10 mg fat, 1 mg cholesterol and 441 mg sodium.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook the pasta according to directions on package.
In a saucepan melt the butter and add the cream.
Bring to a boil whisking constantly.
Reduce heat and add parmesan, nutmeg and about 2 Tbsp. chopped fresh parsley.
Pour sauce over pasta individually.
Serve 6.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar in small mixing bowl.
Add flour and walnuts; mix to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned.
Blend sugar with cream cheese in small mixing bowl until smooth.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well; spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; cool.
Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: roast beef
directions: Place roast in Pyrex dish.
Place on rack in electric roaster. Set meat thermometer at 150°.
Place on top of meat.
Cook 24 hours.

title: cheap and simple sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with onions until onions are transparent. Drain.
Add ketchup, water and cracker crumbs.
Cook for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve on buns or bread.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts.
Chill well.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop onions and peppers.
Cover with boiling vinegar.
Let stand 18 minutes.
Drain cover with boiling water again and bring to a boil.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain well and add salt, vinegar and sugar.
Heat and bring to a boiling point and reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal at once.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix and marinate brisket overnight in a cooking bag.
Cook about 4 hours for 6 pound brisket in oven at about 300°.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and soda.
Melt 2/3 cup butter and mix into it.
Spread 1 cup mixture into 8 x 8-inch pan and microwave 3 to 3 1/2 minutes until bubbly and cooking.
Dump out on foil.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and baking soda.
Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: mandarin delight
directions: Drain both cans well.
Mix everything together.
Put in a 9x13 pan.
Refrigerate 2-3 hours.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Boil cauliflower in salted water for 4 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add cooked cauliflower, sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Toss lightly; saute until a golden brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in a thin dish (quiche dish or casserole dish).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then broil for 5 minutes, or until top is brown.
Serve warm with crackers or cocktail ryes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini. Mix lightly but well. Next add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder. Mix until well blended and add nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Cook 45 minutes at 350° in preheated oven. Makes 2 loaves.

title: crunch drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in flour mixture, cereal and coconut.
I mix this with my hands.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: easy graham cracker refrigerator cake
directions: Prepare chocolate and vanilla pudding as directed; set aside. Open box of graham crackers.
Spread crackers in bottom of a large, oblong dish.
Spread generous layer of chocolate pudding over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and a generous layer of vanilla pudding.
Alternate
until crackers and pudding are used, ending with pudding on top.
When ready to serve, top with sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Then cut into squares.

title: chevre a l'hoice d'olive(goat cheese marinated in olive oil and herbs)
directions: Cut cheese into 1-inch disks and put in a wide mouth jar that holds about 2 cups.
The French "workers glasses" that come with orange or blue plastic lids are particularly nice to use and are available in many stores.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain off grease.
In a 5-quart pan, add meat, onion, salt, pepper, 1 teaspoon chili powder, tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar.
Simmer 1 hour on low heat, then add mushrooms, chili beans and rest of chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes more.

title: amish barbecue pork chops
directions: Pour over pork chops and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: For marinade, combine all ingredients except steak.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over steak in shallow baking dish.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Broil steak over hot coals or in oven for 5 to 8 minutes on each side, depending on desired doneness.
Cut in very thin slices diagnally across the grain.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the apples.
Add apples to the mix until evenly coated.
Place in a 9-inch pie shell.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine everything except yogurt and sugar. Mix yogurt and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.

title: dough for molding
directions: Stir together cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water in a bowl. Mix in a saucepan 2 cups salt and 2/3 cup water, over low heat, until mixture is very warm.
Stir cornstarch mixture into water and salt mixture.
When this gets quite warm and is the consistency of stiff dough, cool, remove from pan and knead like bread.
Knead food coloring into dough.
Store in plastic bag at room temperature.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients for one minute.
This sauce is very good on chicken or pork.

title: german cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt German sweet chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, 1 egg, flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Set this aside also. Beat 2 eggs.
Add sugar, baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix well. Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts, almond extract and vanilla.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Spread remaining in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Pour
the 1 cup set aside over cheese.
Swirl to marble.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cauliflower broccoli bake
directions: Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and 1/4 stick butter and heat until smooth.
Add rice and mix in vegetables.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tollerini
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch skillet; drain off fat. Add next 7 ingredients to beef. Simmer over medium-low heat for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, fill a 2-quart saucepan half full of water. Bring to a boil over high heat. Add noodles to boiling water (add 1 teaspoon salt if desired). Boil 10 minutes; drain. Remove meat from heat; pour contents of skillet in large casserole. Pour noodles over top and mix well. Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pineapple nog
directions: Combine pineapple, eggs, coconut cream, milk and nutmeg in container
of
electric
blender.
Cover.
Whirl
on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into 2 large glasses.
Sprinkle each with additional nutmeg.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Place pieces of frozen dough in well buttered Bundt pan.
Pour melted oleo over frozen dough.
Then sprinkle with mixture of dry pudding, sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Leave out overnight covered. In the morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Sweeten fruit to taste.
Combine other ingredients and pour into pan.
Distribute fruit evenly over batter and bake at 375° to 400° until brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, water and salt in a 2-quart microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Cook an additional 2 minutes.
Remove and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.

title: shrimp sauce piquant
directions: This sauce is excellent on a lettuce leaf cup with boiled shrimp.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole (except cornflakes).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Mix crushed cornflakes with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole and return to oven until lightly brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper, onions and rice together, stirring constantly.
Add olives, salt, pepper, tomato paste and water.
Bake, covered, about one hour at 375°.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and cut up 6 to 7 apples.
Fill pie pan 2/3 full. Sprinkle with walnuts, 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
In bowl, beat
flour, 1 cup sugar, egg, butter and salt.
Cover apples. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: breckenridge (colorado) broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon bits.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Toss with broccoli mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese brunch spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on English muffin, bagel, toast, etc.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix and cream together Miracle Whip with sugar.
Add hot water.
Sift flour, soda, cocoa and salt.
Mix together with Miracle Whip mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sunday sausage
directions: Cook rice as directed.
(Note: 1 large bag of Success rice equals 3 cups cooked rice.)
Prepare the celery, onions and green pepper. Saute in margarine, stirring constantly until slightly tender. Drain on paper towel.
Add soup to boiling water and let stand. Brown sausage until redness is gone.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Place in 9 x 13 casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger frypan supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally. Yield: 6 servings.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the beaten egg and molasses.
Sift in the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill. Roll into small balls.
Dip each in sugar.
Place on greased pan. Dot with cold water, pressing each down.
Bake for 12 minutes in the oven at 350°.

title: cecilia's cranberry salad
directions: Heat juice from crushed pineapple and water.
Mix with Jell-O and add crushed pineapple.
Add 1/2 cup lemon juice, cranberry sauce, nuts and orange peel.
Mix and let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well in
the center.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly; turn out onto floured bread board or waxed paper.
Turn 3-4 times.
Pat out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In baking dish, put rice (cooked), sugar, eggs, milk, raisins and flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: salmon in crust
directions: Roll pastry dough into a 9 x 12-inch rectangle and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Mix together all ingredients except yolk, water and sesame seed.
Place salmon mixture down the center of the dough rectangle.
Fold the sides toward the center and pinch them together, forming a seam.
Mix together the egg yolk and water; brush the top of the rectangle.
Sprinkle sesame seed on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and water until done.
Add sugar and jello.
Boil 1 minute or until dissolved.
Put in jars; cool, then freeze.

title: italian ham pie(makes two pies)
directions: Beat eggs and stir in rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
After pies are done, take out of oven and brush on this mixture: 1 egg, beaten; mix into egg a dash of sugar and bake in 350° oven for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: grandma's pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough into teaspoon sized balls, place on cookie sheet and bake in slow oven; do not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar immediately.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: teriyaki beef kabobs
directions: Prepare marinade; combine brown sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice, oil, ginger and garlic.
Stir in beef.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours, stirring often.
Thirty minutes before serving, thread meat and pineapple on skewers.
Broil 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix the flour, melted oleo and grated nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let crust cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package instructions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and top with the crushed soda crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chiliquillas
directions: Place tortillas on a baking sheet and bake at 300°, turning once, until crisp.
Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine soup, chilies and broth.
Put some soup mixture in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Break up 2 tortillas over the soup.
Sprinkle with onion and top with 1/3 of the chicken.
Top with 1/3 cup cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Cover and bake until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serve and top with chopped tomato, shredded lettuce and pass salsa.
Serves 4.

title: savory crescent squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add next 6 ingredients. Mix well. Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles. Press perforations together. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into center. Seal edges (and slope a bit). Brush tops with butter and spread seasoned crouton crumbs on top. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden. Squares can be partially baked and frozen for later use. Just thaw and finish cooking before serving.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed and bake as cupcakes or in layer pans at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2 (8-inch) round pans with cooking spray.
In a bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In a saucepan, melt corn oil spread; stir in sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan. Stir, then add dry ingredients.
Whisk until well blended.
Pour evenly into pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool.
Fill and frost with Light Frosting as follows.

title: greek chicken
directions: Dice onions and place in the bottom of a pan. Put chicken on top of onions, and salt. Peel, dice and salt and pepper potatoes. Add this on top of chicken. Add canned tomatoes on top of potatoes. Add oregano and olive oil on top of potatoes. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours, at 350 degrees.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and light brown sugar.
Add egg yolk and flour. Mix and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until lightly browned.
Melt a 10 ounce chocolate bar.
Spread on hot crust.
Sprinkle top with pecans.
Cut in small squares while still warm.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Place cooked spaghetti in casserole.
In a small bowl, beat milk and eggs.
Pour over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Then spread spaghetti sauce over top.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook the carrots just until done, but still firm.
Mix together the tomato soup, sugar, oil, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add onions and peppers.
Drain carrots and mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep for about 2 weeks.
Best to prepare a day in advance.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad dressing; add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water; mix well.
Bake at 350°
until top springs back when touched lightly in center.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients very well, then chill before serving.

title: cally's favorite chicken dinner
directions: Heat chicken fat in saucepan.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in chicken soup and broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Add chicken.
Heat through.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine biscuit mix and sage.
Stir in milk.
Drop by tablespoon onto chicken mixture. Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: lemon pie (tart)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and boil for 10 minutes; mix juice of lemons, egg yolks and cornstarch until smooth.
Add to water mixture; add butter and stir until thickened.
Pour into cooled pie shell and top with meringue made from 2 egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar (beat until stiff peaks form).
Spread over filling, sealing to crust.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in the order they are listed. Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise. Next sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise.
Top with bacon. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: barbecued london broil
directions: Treat meat with tenderizer according to jar directions.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce.
Place flank steak on broiler pan without rack.
Pour half the sauce over meat.
Broil 5 minutes, basting once with sauce. Turn meat over.
Broil 5 minutes more for rare; 7 for medium.
Baste with remaining sauce. Cut into thin slices crosswise against grain on diagonal.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn flakes muffins
directions: Stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
Measure Kellogg's corn flakes cereal and milk into large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine; let stand about 2 minutes, or until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil; beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: stove top barbecue beef
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or heavy saucepot, heat oil and brown beef in two batches.
Remove and set aside; reserve drippings. Add carrots, green pepper and chili powder to reserved drippings and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 2 minutes.
Stir in soup mix blended with water, tomato sauce, brown sugar and cider vinegar.
Return beef to Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 2 1/2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Stir in hot pepper sauce. Using 2 forks, shred beef.
Serve on rolls.
May be reheated. Makes about 8 servings.

title: blethen house cookies(secret recipe since 1845)
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for 1/2 an hour.

title: apple dumplins(baked)
directions: Make dough and roll out to about 1/4-inch thick. Spread finely chopped apples evenly over dough. Dot apples with butter. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place in buttered pan. Pour 1/2 syrup over all slices. Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Halfway through baking, repeat pouring syrup over dumplings. Serve warm.

title: jo ann gibson's chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Cool.
Blend in sugar and eggs.
Add flour, vanilla and chocolate.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Put into muffin papers to bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add pretzels and press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and one carton of Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mix.

title: crab imperial
directions: Toss lightly crabmeat, green peppers, pimento, egg and bread crumbs.
Combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper, Old Bay seasoning, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce to make a mayonnaise mixture. Toss mayonnaise mixture lightly with crabmeat mixture.
Mound in 4 or 5 individual shells or place in a small casserole.
Mix mayonnaise with a small amount of milk and spread over the crab. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Early in day, mix all ingredients thoroughly by hand.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Form into 1-inch balls. Fry in 1 cup of hot oil over high heat until cooked and browned.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Stir all ingredients together until orange juice and strawberries thaw.
Put in container and freeze.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Heat soup as it comes from the can.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add seasoning.
Stir in stuffing mix and celery.
Bake in greased 1 or 1 1/2-quart covered casserole for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: mary's best bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add soup and wine; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and smooth.
Add green beans and almonds; mix well and season to taste.
Turn into a greased casserole; sprinkle with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot and lightly browned.

title: wild rice chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice. Blend in soup, mushrooms, soy sauce, chicken, broth, celery, onions and water chestnuts. Spread in 13 x 9 baking dish. In small bowl, combine dry stuffing mix and melted butter. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Wash kraut in colander and drain.
Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.

title: b.t.s. chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
With a wooden spoon handle, poke holes in warm cake.
Pour condensed milk into the holes, then pour ice cream topping into same holes. Cool.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars. Refrigerate.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add kidney beans and cool.
When cool, add remaining ingredients (don't add Tostitos until almost ready to serve; they get soft). Serve with taco sauce.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Melt the butterscotch morsels with the butter in top of double boiler. Remove from heat.
Stir in the brown sugar and cool for 5 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla and beat. Blend in sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: matzo brei (for two)
directions: Soak matzos in lukewarm milk or water until soft. Drain well. Stir in eggs, salt and pepper.

Heat butter in an 8-inch skillet, pour in mixture, cover and cook over moderate heat until the underside is well browned, about 10 minutes. Turn carefully with a spatula or pancake turner; brown the other side. Serve hot with honey, maple syrup or sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Heat buttermilk (do not boil).
Drop in yeast cake or dry yeast and let dissolve.
Add oil and mix.
Add salt and sugar. Sift in flour as needed and knead at the same time.
Add flour to make up a good dough.
Knead well.
Pinch off 3 small balls (English walnut size).
Roll in hands, then place in muffin tin. Let rise.
Bake at 425° until well browned.

title: oven fried chicken, another way
directions: Roll chicken pieces in oil; then roll in mixture of cracker meal, Accent, salt and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes, or until fork can be inserted with ease.

title: sweet plastic pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water overnight.
Drain and soak in salt water for 4 hours.
Soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Bring to boil in alum water.
Drain and wash.

title: broccoli-nut casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli according to package directions.
Drain. Add soup,
mayonnaise
and
peanuts.
Mix
well.
Add eggs and onion. Mix
well.	Melt
butter
and
pour over bread crumbs. Pour broccoli
mixture into greased 1 1/2 or 2 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla flakes
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick like pudding.
Let cool.
Cream and add sugar, Crisco and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Make dressing of sour cream, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over thinly sliced cucumbers and onions.

title: sesame asparagus canapes
directions: Remove crusts from bread and flatten each slice of bread with a rolling pin. Spread each slice with the soft Boursin cheese. Place asparagus spear on top of each and roll up. Cut into thirds. Dip in melted butter. Roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and sesame seeds. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes. Can be frozen and reheated.

title: tuna dip
directions: Gradually add salad dressing to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, adding frozen coconut. Bake as directed.
While cake is warm, glaze with following glaze.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a punch bowl.
Makes a very refreshing party drink.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream oleo with sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Add bananas, nuts and sour cream.
Gradually add dry ingredients and mix at low speed one-half minute until blended. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: tomato bread
directions: Cut the top crust off of the French bread and place on a foiled cookie sheet.

title: whole-wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine margarine, molasses, honey and salt.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let dough rest a few minutes.
Shape into 4 loaves.
Place in greased bread pans.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 loaves.

title: turkey chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat 1 tablespoon of oil and brown turkey.

title: ham-green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; stir in soup and heat about 2 minutes.
Add rice, beans, ham and seasonings.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix burger, olives, onions, peppers and seasonings together. Place half of corn chips in bottom of pie crust.
Spread burger mix over corn chips.
Spread with sour cream.
Cover with grated cheese.
Sprinkle remaining corn chips.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Then sprinkle shredded lettuce over top and arrange tomato wedges and avocado slices nicely around middle of pie.

title: no egg wonder cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until almost smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Let cool in pan.

title: nutty noodly's
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and butterscotch bits, stirring occasionally.
When thoroughly melted, remove from heat and add chow mein noodles and nuts (if desired) and coat noodles with melted mixture thoroughly.
Spoon out on wax papered covered cookie sheet and place in refrigerator until firm. Place in tightly covered container and could be stored in refrigerator if you would like.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Beat in mixer for 2 minutes.
Keeps forever.
Good with ham.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Mix sugar and zucchini in blender, add lemon juice.
Bring to boil and boil hard for full 20 minutes.
Add jello and stir well. Put in hot jars (pints) and seal.
Makes about 3 pints.
Use a large kettle to cook in.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup. Stir well. Bring to boil. Stir in milk. Simmer, stirring constantly. Stir in vanilla. Pour over popcorn. Butter hands and shape into balls.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Core and steam cabbage.
When wilted and cooled, peel off leaves.
Mix together raw beef, sausage, onion, cooked rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Put some of the mixture on a leaf and roll up like a sausage.
Place in large baking dish (8 1/2 x 13-inch) and cover with mixture of butter, hot water and cream of tomato soup.
Dot with a little butter, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 300 to 350° until meat is done.

title: pudding lush
directions: Mix flour and margarine like pie crust; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: favorite breakfast casserole
directions: * I suggest 10 ounces Barrel Mellow.

title: honey pound cake
directions: Set out 2 eggs to warm at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Set aside 3 bowls (1 large and 2 small) and a baking pan, 6 x 3 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch, greased and floured.

title: couscous(a north african dish that can feed a crowd, 4 to 6 servings.)
directions: In vegetable oil, cook meat.
Saute garlic with the meat.
Add carrots, onions, turnips, tomatoes, salt, tomato paste, peppers, water, bouillon, cumin, thyme and bay leaf.
Make a mixture of remaining spices.
Blend well and use 3/4 teaspoon of mixture in the sauce (more or less to taste).
Cook vegetables and seasonings with meat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add zucchini, chickpeas and cabbage.
Cook until done.
This recipe can be doubled or tripled as needed.
Couscous grains can be found in the supermarket, Near East brand.
Cook couscous grains.
Put sauce over the grains in individual servings.
Warm raisins can be sprinkled over the servings.

title: grandma's christmas sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flavorings and then stir in the dry ingredients.
Chill dough until it is stiff enough to work with (at least 3 hours).
Working with a portion of the dough, keep the rest refrigerated until ready to use.
Knead a couple of times until dough is pliable and roll out on floured table to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in shapes and bake in 350° oven until the cookies just start to brown at the edges.
Do not overbake.
Cool and frost or decorate with colored sugar before baking.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.
Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Form ball. Chop green onion tops and sprinkle on top. Chill and serve.

title: robin's swiss deer steaks
directions: Pound deer steaks with meat mallet.
Salt and pepper both sides, dip in flour and fry in oil, in frying pan.
Lightly brown each side, does not have to cook red out of meat.
Place in baking dish, after all meat has been cooked (add more oil if needed). Pour most oil out of frying pan. Add onions, stir add flour (to make gravy).
Pour in water and sauce.
Mix, may not set up as thick as gravy.
Pour over meat, and bake at 350° for 1-2 hours until can cut with fork.

title: company carrots
directions: Slice carrots; cook and drain.
Put in a 2-quart casserole. Add onion and green pepper.
Set aside.
Combine in saucepan the remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes; pour over carrot mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seekh kabobs
directions: Wash mutton and put twice through mincer.
Add to it the green chilies, ginger and garlic.
Then salt, pepper and onion.
Mix spices well in the mincer and make kabobs in the form of ping-pong ball size and shape.
Push skewers through kabobs.
Pat and mold until mince clings around skewers.

title: grape parfait
directions: Spoon vanilla ice cream in the bottom of parfait glasses (about 2 heaping teaspoonfuls).
Next, put 1 or 2 teaspoons of thawed grape juice (do not dilute the juice with water).
Add another layer of ice cream.
Top with grape juice for top layer. Cover with foil and freeze.
When ready to serve, let them soften slightly and pour 7-Up over top.

title: cherry crumb cake i
directions: Mix flour and sugar with baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter, add the egg, and mix to make crumbs.
Place half of crumbs into sheet cake pan, pour can of pie filling over, and sprinkle remaining half of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes.

title: chicken brunch casserole
directions: In a large bowl, toss bread crumbs and chicken broth. Add chicken, rice, pimentos, parsley and salt. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Pour beaten eggs over all. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour, uncovered. Let set a few minutes before cutting into squares or slices.

title: okra creole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large stock pot.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: root beer float
directions: Pour 1/2 cup root beer or cola into 16 ounce soda glass and spoon ice cream into glass. Top with remaining root beer or cola.

title: norwegian kringla
directions: Cream butter and sugar together with mixer.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
May have to mix by hand by the time the last cup of flour is added.
When mixed well, chill dough overnight in the refrigerator.
When baking, take a 1/2 to 3/4 tablespoon of dough and touch lightly into some flour.
Roll out (with hands) to a length of 8 to 10 inches on a clean, lightly floured area of countertop or table.
Take string and form a pretzel shape (or an 8) on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for about 5 minutes. Can put them in the broiler for a few seconds to brown them a little.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure flour and sift.
Add salt and baking powder.
Sift 4 times and set aside.
Measure sugar and set aside.
Cream oil and butter.
Add part of sugar and cream until sugar and eggs are gone.
Add 1/3 flour and half of milk with flavoring in it, 1/3 flour, rest of milk and last of flour.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar and margarine as you would pie crust.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes; cool.
Crumble and sprinkle in 9 x 13-inch pan leaving crumbs loose.
Don't pat down.
Beat 3/4 cup butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese all together and spread over crumbs. Spread chopped nuts on top.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; add strawberries, juice and all.
Chill until mixture is almost set. Pour over nuts.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts. Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Make jello and let thicken until like egg whites.
Add strawberries, cut up or mashed.
Add drained, crushed pineapple, softened cream cheese and walnuts together and fold into the Cool Whip.
In jello mold, layer jello, then Cool Whip, the jello, etc., ending with jello on top.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: oniony potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
Coat with vegetable oil, then with onion soup mix.
Bake in greased casserole dish for about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Ritz crackers and butter.
Mix well and place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Combine oleo and crackers; place on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until onion is tender and casserole is bubbly. Serves 8.

title: almond punch
directions: Mix all except ginger ale.
You may freeze the punch base in ziploc bags until ready to use.
Let partially thaw before serving.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and cook over heat until thick. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Pour back into saucepan and cook until thick. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup and boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and stir.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper or pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange marmalade cake
directions: Heat marmalade in a saucepan over low heat until liquified. Cool.
Add egg, milk and shortening.
Stir mixture into sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mama ann's sunday chicken
directions: Flour and season chicken.
Brown in shortening.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Add soup to skillet in which chicken was browned.
Add curry powder and mushrooms; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind or chop cranberries and apples in food processor.
Mix all ingredients except cream and let chill overnight.
Next morning, whip cream and fold into cranberry mixture.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: our favorite apple kuchen
directions: Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Thicken before adding next layer.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with cornflakes or crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable rice pie
directions: Combine rice, cheese, 1/4 cup salad dressing and egg; mix well.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix crackers and butter for crust.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Mix dry dessert topping.
Fold into cream cheese.
Chill overnight.
Top with cherry pie filling. Optional:
Sprinkle crumbs on top.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Tear cake into small pieces and fold in with other ingredients lightly.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Mix boiling water and Jell-O together; let cool.
Mix all together and freeze.
When ready to serve, get out of freezer several hours ahead of time.
Place in punch bowl; add 2 bottles ginger ale and mix.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in blueberry pie filling. Sift together dry ingredients; add to blueberry mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into middle comes out clean.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts.
Stir in rice and broccoli; pour into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a 9 x 9-inch glass baking dish (do not grease).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops and brown rice
directions: Brown pork chops in hot fat in pressure pan.
Place rice in hot fat.
Stir constantly until well browned.
Add tomatoes, seasoning, chopped onion and green pepper.
Stir well.
Add pork chops and water.

title: chile verde burritos
directions: In skillet, add 1 tablespoon oil and heat.
Add pork, one pound at a time, and brown.
Place meat in a 4-quart saucepan and set aside.

title: diabetic raisin nut cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x
4-inch cake pan. Cream the margarine and applesauce.
Add egg and vanilla to mixture and blend well.
Stir in dry ingredients (artificial sweetener, flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves, raisins and pecans). Bake mixture for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil the brown sugar and Karo until sugar dissolves.
Add the margarine and Eagle Brand milk.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until firm ball stage.
Add the soda (will foam up).
Stir, then pour over the popped corn.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the spinach and the broccoli a little less than the box says.
Add a tablespoon of vinegar to each.
Add the sessonings to the soups, then fold in the drained spinach and broccoli.
Pour into 10-inch buttered casserole and arrange the onions and tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, tomatoes, onion and broth together to make sauce. Bring just to a boil. It will thicken. Set aside. Line casserole dish with 1/2 Doritos and 1/2 cup cheese (shredded) on top of chicken. Pour sauce over all, then put remaining Doritos on top and sprinkle cheese on top. Place in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter with a little water and put in broccoli. Add other ingredients, rice being last.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees until brown (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).

title: red coffee
directions: Put sugar, cinnamon sticks, cloves and allspice in coffee filter basket of coffeemaker.
Fill pot with juices and water, let perk and serve.
Makes 20 cups!
(Large coffee maker.)

title: deep dish chicken pot pie(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large saucepan, cook celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, bouillon and pepper; add 4 1/2 cups milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in chicken, carrots, potatoes and peas; remove from heat.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining milk and biscuit mix; mix well. Turn 2/3 of dough into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish; sprinkle with flour.
With floured hands, pat evenly over bottom and up sides of dish.
Pour chicken mixture into prepared dish. Turn remaining dough onto a well-floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into eight 3-inch rounds; arrange on top of casserole.
If desired, beat together egg yolk and water.
Brush on rounds.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and Cheddar cheese in cubes.
Add olives, cubed avocado and nuts.
Fold in salad dressing (not too much). Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: wilted leaf lettuce
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble, reserving drippings. Add onion to drippings; cook until tender.
Add vinegar, 1/4 cup water, sugar, sprinkle of salt and bacon.
Cook and stir until it boils.
Place lettuce in bowl, pour hot dressing over, garnish with radishes and egg.

title: stell's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix in large bowl the butter and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients: flour, baking powder, soda, salt and lemon extract. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown in floured and greased tube pan.
Can use 13 x 9-inch pan (bake about 45 minutes).

title: hungarian mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Add the mushrooms, dill, 1/2 cup of the stock, soy sauce and paprika. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: shannon's blueberry muffins(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. In a separate bowl, combine wet ingredients; stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients. Add in just enough milk to make a cake-like batter. Mix in blueberries. Pour batter into greased large muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Mix all ingredients in a buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbara's soup beans(crock-pot)
directions: Sort beans in bowl; rinse.
Put beans in a large pan; cover with water.
Boil rapidly for 10 to 15 minutes.
(This swells the beans.)
Rinse and put in crock-pot with the ham chunks.
Add a little salt.
Cover with water.
Cook on high for 8 to 10 hours.

title: green beans and bacon
directions: Set
aside
cooked
bacon.
Heat
all
ingredients in a 12-inch Dutch
oven to boiling, 10 coals on top and 6 coals on bottom.
Add bacon last as garnish.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add potato water and mashed potatoes. Beat eggs.
Add to mixture along with the remaining ingredients. Cover with towel.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down. Knead and make into rolls.
Cover rolls with butter (lightly). Cover pans with towel.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix and chill 2 hours.
Wonderful with vegetables.

title: cape cod clam cakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, eggs, milk and seasonings into a batter.
Stir in the clams, mixing thoroughly.
Drop from spoon into deep, hot fat and cook for 1 minute or until golden brown. Richer cakes may be made by using 1/2 cup clam liquor and reducing the milk listed to 1/2 cup.
This recipe serves 4.

title: pork chops with peaches
directions: In heavy skillet, saute chops in oil until golden brown on both sides, then season with salt and pepper.
Combine orange and lemon juices with honey, cinnamon and ginger and pour over chops. Cover tightly and cook for 20 minutes over medium heat.
Add peaches; cover and cook until heated through (about 10 minutes). Remove chops and peaches; reduce sauce, if desired, and pour over chops and peaches.
Serve.
Makes 3 servings.

title: cheese cakes
directions: Scald sweet and sour milk. Strain through cheesecloth to curd. Add sugar, yolks of eggs (slightly beaten), lemon and salt.
Line patty pans with paste.
Fill with mixture and sprinkle with chopped almonds.
Bake until mixture is firm to the touch.

title: spaghetti dish
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Saute onion. Grease baking dish.
Cut up tomatoes.
Layer twice as follows: spaghetti, tomatoes, onion and cheese.

title: irish soda bread #2
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart round casserole.

title: impossible zucchini pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first 6 items together and place in pie plate.
Beat last 5 items until smooth and pour over vegetable mixture.
Cook for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: crispy flounder fillets
directions: Combine sesame seed, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper in 9-inch pie plate.
Combine egg white and water in second 9-inch pie plate.
Dip fish first into egg white mixture, then into sesame seed mixture, coating both sides.
Place on waxed paper.
Panfry half of fish in 1 1/2 tablespoons of oil in skillet over high heat on one side for 3 minutes.
Turn over and cook 2 minutes longer or until fish is white in center and flakes easily.
Transfer to platter and keep warm.
Clean skillet well with paper towel before frying second batch.
Add remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons of oil before frying.

title: baked beans(easy.  good.)
directions: I found that the liquid (not fat) from the broiled bacon is very flavorable, so I add some to the mixture and use only 1 pound of bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 2 hours at 325°.
If too soupy, bake longer.
Do not turn up the heat.
The beans will cook up and become mushy.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender and let them cool for 20 minutes.
Peel potatoes and slice them, laying them in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon to cover.
Repeat this procedure again, laying potatoes on top of one another.
Place pieces of margarine to cover the last layer of potatoes.

title: picante chicken
directions: Brown chicken in Pam or 1 tablespoon oil.
Dissolve bouillon in 1 cup water.
Add quartered orange, rice and picante.
Add more water if too dry before rice is done.
Cook about 20 minutes on stove.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in buttered dish.

title: sausage casserole
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, celery and bouillon cubes until tender and drain.
Add the milk, Velveeta cheese, flour and butter.
Mix well until melted and blended well.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Take left over beef 'n cut up in pieces...add taters 'n onions thet hav bin cut up in tiny pieces...pore in sum beef stock 'n cook.

title: chilli beans
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until well seasoned through.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Cook and grate potatoes.
Cook onions, chopped fine, and celery, chopped fine, in 1/4 cup oleo until brown.
Add cream of celery soup, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, bacon bits and salt to taste.
Pour over grated potatoes.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake until heated through approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese after baked.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in microwave oven approximately 1 1/2 minutes. Stir in salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese wafers(makes 75)
directions: Mix butter, flour and cheese all together with your hands, then roll out on floured board and cut with a very small biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and brush tops with beaten egg. Put a pecan on top of each and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
As soon as you take them out of oven, sprinkle them with salt and remove from cookie sheet.
These are delicious as snacks and tidbits.
You may leave the pecans off some of them for variety. They are just as good.

title: grandma kohn's chili sauce
directions: Pour boiling water over tomatoes for 2 minutes, then skin. Combine everything and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be water bath processed or frozen. Use with pasta or as an accompaniment to meat.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.

title: brunch punch
directions: Bring the sugar and water to a boil.
Be sure all the sugar is dissolved.
Pour over lemonade and orange juice.
Pour 1/2 of the pineapple juice into a blender.
Add large pieces of banana; puree.
Add to juice mixture with remaining pineapple juice. Freeze in 2 large Ziploc bags for easier access.
Thaw approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour before placing in punch bowl. Add the 2 liter bottles of ginger ale.

title: after dinner mint pineapple
directions: Cut fresh pineapple into chunks and marinate in creme de menthe for about 2 hours.
Spear each chunk with pick and serve from deep bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap until ready to serve.

title: mini blini
directions: Remove crusts from bread slices and roll thin.
Cut each piece of bread in half, spread with cream cheese and roll up.
Dip in melted butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Freeze.

title: cake in an orange(method:  coals)
directions: Slice orange off 1/3 down from the top.
Spoon fruit out of bottom 2/3 of the orange, leaving an empty shell.
Prepare the cake mix according to box directions.
Fill each orange shell halfway with batter.
Place in coals to cook.
It may take 10 to 15 minutes (can be done in reflector oven).
Gingerbread mix is real good.

title: hot tomato juice with lemon floaters
directions: In saucepan, combine all but lemon.
Heat to just boiling. Serve in mugs with lemon slices as floaters in each.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Blend at low speed to moisten.
