Scrape sides of bowl.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes. Pour into 10-inch tube pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Cool.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Rinse 2 cans of pinto beans and drain.
Put rest of ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole and mix thoroughly.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: tortilla swirls
directions: Mix chopped items with cream cheese.
Spread mixture on flour tortillas.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Secure rolls tight with toothpicks.
Refrigerate until cold.
Slice rolls into circles and arrange on platter.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each section in melted butter. Roll in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Drop in tube or bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Sprinkle pecans as you layer the sections.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, sugar, salt and shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough. Turn out on floured surface and knead until smooth (about 10 minutes).
Shape in a ball.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease surface of dough.
Cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 1/4 hours).
Punch down. Shape into desired dinner rolls or make 2 loaves.

title: baked alaska
directions: Spread ice cream on sponge cake and put in freezer until ready to serve.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until very stiff. Gradually add the sugar, beating constantly.
Fold in vanilla flavoring.
Remove the cake from the freezer and cover with the meringue.
Be sure that the meringue completely covers all the ice cream.
Bake for 4-5 minutes in a preheated 475° oven or until meringue is slightly brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening until creamy.
Gradually add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and bananas alternately.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: skillet kraut
directions: Cut salt pork into small pieces.
In 10-inch skillet over low heat, brown the salt pork, stirring occasionally.
Pour off fat. Remove salt pork.
Melt the oleo over low heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring often, until golden.
Add sauerkraut, water, brown sugar, vinegar and salt pork.
Cover and simmer until liquid has evaporated, about 1/2 hour.
This is especially good when served with picnic foods or buffet foods.

title: pizza sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients except American cheese. Spread mixture on cut side of bread. Place on cookie sheet. Broil with door open until done (about 10 minutes). Cut cheese diagonally; place on meat mixture. Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix
ingredients together.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix kraut, carrots, celery, green pepper, onion and pimento. In a jar or small bowl, combine sugar and oil. Pour over vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into (Pam sprayed) two round pans or one oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and split into layers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together and bake about one hour at 325°.

title: pie filling
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together well.
Add water and stir until clear over heat.
Boil 20 minutes.

title: butterscotch crunch squares
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar; cut in margarine until mixture resembles crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir while still warm to crumble; cool.
Spread half the crumbs in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan; drizzle about half the ice cream topping over crumbs in pan.
Stir ice cream to soften; spoon carefully into pan.
Drizzle with remaining topping; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.

title: snicker surprises
directions: 1) Combine butter, peanut butter and sugar using a mixer on med. or low, until light and fluffy.

title: pretzel cake
directions: Mix the crushed pretzels with the melted butter and 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Press in square or oblong pan; cook for 8 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: cookies 'n cream torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom and sides of jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch, with shortening. Make cake mix. Pour into pan. Bake 25 to 33 minutes. Run knife around sides of pan to loosen cake. Cool completely in pan on wire rack about 1 hour. Fold crushed cookies into whipped topping. Cut cake crosswise in half. Remove one cake half from pan, using wide spatula to life cake; place on serving plate. Spread cake with half of the whipped topping mixture. Top with other
half of cake; spread with remaining whipped topping mixture. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: sausage and cheese quiche
directions: Mix liquid and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into one deep dish pie shell (unbaked).
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set and firm.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix and place by teaspoonful onto cookie sheets.
Dampen bottom of glass.
Place in sugar and flatten cookies.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt cheese, Worcestershire sauce and almonds into can of mushroom soup.
Add beans to this mixture and toss.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle top sparingly with red pepper.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° until heated through.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix together potatoes, mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Put into a buttered baking dish or pan (9 x 13-inch).
Top with bacon that has been partially cooked to remove some of the fat and water and the sliced olives.
Bake for one hour at 325°.
Can be prepared a day ahead, refrigerated and baked just prior to serving (may need to increase baking time).
Also delicious as leftover the following day.
Just reheat the refrigerated salad.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Note:
All ingredients must be at room temperature.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush the cookies.
Save 2 cups for topping. Combine crumbs and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream (soft enough to spread) and place on crumbs.
Top with fudge topping and then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Place in freezer.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 sheet pans, approximately 150 servings.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover meat with water; steam for 30 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup water to butter.
Add celery, green peppers and onion.
Cover and steam 5 or 8 minutes.
Combine vegetables with the meat.
Add mushrooms, Chinese molasses and sauce.
Add cornstarch mix.
Cook until boiling point.
Cook gently for about 5 minutes.

title: grandma's 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and 7-Up until blended. Bake in three 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients. Serve with fish.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat thoroughly in a small amount of oil.
Cook until tender.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add bouillon, soy sauce and garlic.
Add green peppers.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes. Thicken slowly with cornstarch and water mixture.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: grandpa's favorite
directions: In medium saucepan, put egg, butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour this mixture over wafers that have been broken into small pieces. Press into greased pan and cool.
Add coconut or nuts for variation, if you wish.

title: dumplings
directions: Add margarine and salt into water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour boiling water over plain flour and work together with a fork.
Let mixture cool for a couple of hours in refrigerator.
Roll out dough and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: party punch
directions: Mix water, jello and sugar.
Add 3 quarts cold water.
Add all lemon and pineapple juices.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend until creamy.
Serve with chips or pretzels.
Makes enough for 20 servings.

title: billy goats
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; then add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add cocoa gradually and mix until blended.
Sift flour and soda into the mixture.
Beat well.
Blend in dates, coconut and rice cereal and mix until all are coated and well dispersed.
Drop batter by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Set aside.
Fry and cut up link sausages or country sausage, drained.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Alternate in bottom of shallow casserole dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread, sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13 pan.
Melt chocolate in double broiler until melted.
Add peanut butter to chocolate until blended.
Pour into pan and let cool at room temperature completely.
Cut into pieces.
Enjoy!

title: taco dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover; chill.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and add M&M's.
Spoon by tablespoon on to a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
This is a good recipe for children to make.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Mix Crisco, salt and vanilla.
Add milk and sugar alternately until smooth.

title: pommes frites(fried potatoes)
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in pan; cover with water and boil until they can be pierced with a table knife.
Drain in strainer or pat them completely dry before drying.
In skillet, heat butter and olive oil over medium-high heat and add potatoes. Brown potatoes on all sides by turning individually.
Cook until golden brown.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Combine rest of ingredients in blender.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate approximately 1 hour.
Bake in marinade at 375° for 1 1/2 hours. If doubling recipe, make only 1 1/2 times marinade.

title: mini-monster jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar until fluffy; add eggs.
Combine flour and baking soda. Blend into creamy mixture.
Stir in M&M's, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough (1 1/2-inch balls), about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes on cookie sheets, then transfer to wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine wafer crumbs with butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press into greased 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.
Beat together 2 packages cream cheese, sugar and flour until creamy smooth.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining cream cheese alternately with the eggs, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and cream.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into pan. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes, then at 250° for 1 hour.
Let stand in turned off oven 1 1/2 hours more.
Open oven door partially and leave in 30 minutes more.
Top will have cracked appearance.
Cool on rack to room temperature.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, remove from pan.
Garnish with chocolate curls or piped on sweet cream cheese.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add all the vegetables and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in broth and seasonings.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in cream and heat through.
Delicious!

title: congealed salad
directions: Add 1/2 can water to pineapple and cook for 10 minutes.
Add jello and mix good.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Beat with mixer and then congeal.

title: potato soup
directions: In

saucepan, saute onion in butter. Add potatoes and barely cover with water; season with salt and pepper and cook until done. Stir in cream of chicken soup, milk and Velveeta. Heat until cheese is completely melted. Garnish with crumbled cooked bacon, chives and grated cheese.

title: batter cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together to make batter.
Melt 1 stick of margarine in baking dish. Pour batter into melted margarine.
Pour fruit over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can use any kind of canned fruit.

title: casserole del-italiano
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350° (glass pan 325°).
Combine cheeses and sour cream with onions.
Layer half the noodles in bottom of pan and top with all cheese mixture (spread evenly).
Top with remaining noodles.
Top with meat sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 8 hours on slow. Can as usual in hot jars.

title: sun corn
directions: Mix ingredients into 3-quart saucepan and simmer on low heat 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: cranberry mallo salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Stir in marshmallows and sugar.
Chill overnight.
Add nuts and apples.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill. Heap on pineapple slices.

title: bacon quiche biscuit cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and eggs on low speed until smooth.
Stir in Swiss cheese and green onions; set aside.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Cream sugar and salad dressing together.
To this mixture add flour, cocoa and baking soda which has been sifted and measured. Next add water, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: ency's dill dip
directions: Combine everything together and refrigerate for 24 hours for flavor.
The next day blend together.
Especially good with cucumbers and zucchini.

title: picante super skillet nachos
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, brown meat with onions; drain.
Add picante sauce, beans and chili powder; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato and avocado; remove from heat.
Sprinkle cheese; spoon sour cream onto center of meat mixture.
Place a row of tortilla chips around edge of skillet; serve immediately with additional chips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese and egg brunch
directions: Break bread into 1-inch pieces.
Place half of bread in buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Over this, spread in layers the mushrooms, olives and cheese.
Spread remaining bread cubes over top.

title: festive chicken(serves 6)
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine cranberry sauce, onion soup mix and salad dressing in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator for several hours.

title: browned rice
directions: Brown onions, rice and beef in oleo.
Add all other ingredients and place in a large baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes on 325°.

title: cocktail crackers
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in grated cheese and butter.
Add milk and mix.
Roll for pastry.
Spread with deviled ham.
Roll like jelly roll.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice thin.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine water and condensed milk and mix. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped whipping cream.
Put vanilla wafers and bananas in bottom of bowl. Put 1/2 pudding mixture over.
Put another layer of wafers and bananas.
Put remaining pudding on top.
Crumble a few wafers and sprinkle over top of pudding and refrigerate.

title: pickle-in-the-middle
directions: Drain sausage and cut each sausage into 3 pieces.
Cut the cheese into small squares, one for each piece of sausage.
Cut the pickles into bite-size pieces, one for each piece of sausage. Push a toothpick through a sausage piece, followed by a pickle piece, then a piece of cheese.
Repeat for all sausage, pickle and cheese pieces.
The pickle's in the middle!

title: red chili puree
directions: Put chilies in a large bowl and cover with boiling water.
Soak for

title: refrigerator watermelon rind pickles
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring often.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer slowly for 45 to 50 minutes, or until rind is tender and translucent.
Cool.
Refrigerate rind with liquid in covered glass container.
Store for at least 12 hours before serving to blend flavors.
Pickles will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: chicken and sour cream casserole
directions: Crumble 1 1/2 sleeves of crackers and sprinkle in bottom of casserole dish. Drizzle melted butter over crackers. After chicken has been cooked and deboned, place chicken meat on top of crackers and butter mixture.

title: raised loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
350° (325° if using glass pans).
Mix yeast in warm
water.
Stir
in
of
flour to make a thin mixture and
let
stand
in
warm
place
minutes or until mixture starts to get light and frothy.
Cream the butter; add sugar gradually
and
beat until fluffy.
Set aside 1/8 cup of flour. Mix
together
remaining flour, baking
powder, spices and salt. Add
to
butter
mixture alternately with the milk, beginning
and ending
with
dry
ingredients.
Add
to yeast mixture.
Dredge raisins in 1/8 cup flour and stir into batter which should
be like thick, whipped
cream; if too thick, add a little milk. Spread batter in greased and floured loaf pans (two).
Bake
about 50
minutes or golden brown.
Remove from pans after 10 minutes. Cool on racks.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in a saucepan over medium heat. Remove from heat and add chow mein noodles and peanuts; coat well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; let set.
Yield: approximately 2 dozen.

title: pork chops(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Dot each chop with butter; sprinkle each with Lipton onion soup mix (dry).
Sprinkle remainder over top while in crock-pot. Cook on low for 9 to 10 hours.
Delicious!

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Cook Eagle Brand, stirring constantly, on medium heat until thick. Add dates and nuts. Spread frosting consisting of oleo, powdered sugar, vanilla and milk. Spread on Ritz crackers (cover completely). Bake 3 to 5 minutes at 375°. Ice with a small amount of white icing.

title: creole style green beans
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Add onion and green pepper to the bacon grease and saute until tender.
Blend in flour, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add tomatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Top with bacon.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Sift flour, salt and soda together and add alternately with sour cream.
Add all flavorings; mix well.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: italian-style cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meats, salt, monosodium, pepper, onions, rice and eggs; mixing well.
Form into 10 to 12 fat rolls (about as long as your thumb).

title: syrup cake
directions: Mix flour and water in last.
Bake at 350°.

title: honey butter
directions: Beat the butter in a small bowl until creamy.
Add the honey and lemon juice; mix well.
Use the butter right away or chill it in a covered bowl.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Add bananas and vanilla; mix well. Sift flour, soda and salt into mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Do not uncover during baking!

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers with oleo to make crust.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick oleo for 10 minutes.
Spread on crust. Slice bananas.
Layer the fruit.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, combine bouillon, water, potatoes, carrots, celery and onion.
Cook 20 minutes on medium to medium high.
Add broccoli and cauliflower.
Cook 20 minutes more.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook on medium-low until cheese melts.
Even better the next day!

title: scotch oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch greased pan.
In medium-sized saucepan, combine oleo and sugar.
Heat while stirring, until oleo melts.
Stir in oats, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn into pan.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly brown.
Remove from oven.
Let cool about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When melted, spread evenly over top.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes 28 (1 x 2-inch) squares.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mash potatoes thoroughly; add egg yolk, salt, cinnamon and butter, mixing well. Shape 6 balls by molding sweet potato mixture around each marshmallow. Beat egg white until foamy. Roll balls in egg white, then in corn flakes. Place in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 10
to 12 minutes until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: bacon and cheddar pinwheels
directions: Roll bread flat with rolling pin (4 pieces at a time).
In small bowl, combine milk, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Lay 3 halves closely together; place bread on top and spread approximately 1 tablespoon of milk mixture on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Roll bacon around bread; secure each piece of bacon with a toothpick.
Chill.

title: twinkie pie
directions: Slice Twinkies and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan to form bottom layer.
Slice bananas over Twinkies.
Prepare pudding according to box directions. Spoon half of the pudding over the bananas and Twinkies. Spoon of the the pineapple on top of the pudding.
Spoon the rest of the pudding on top of the pineapple.
Cover with all of the Cool Whip and garnish with nuts.

title: cranberry sauce salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cranberry sauce and beat together with wire whip. Add pineapple.
I cool until starting to thicken, then add apples.
Pour into dish or mold.
Chill until firm; can top with Cool Whip.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Put a layer of Doritos in bottom of baking dish.
Mix chili with ground beef.
Put a layer of chili beef mixture on Doritos, then a layer of grated cheese. Continue to layer with remaining Doritos and chili beef mixture and cheese on top of layers.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger noodle skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and beef. Cook, stirring with a fork to break up meat, until beef is browned and onion is tender.
Drain.

title: golden oats oven fried chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, melt butter with garlic. Dip chicken in batter then in oat mixture. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: beef ribs
directions: Brown ribs in oil in Dutch oven.
In bowl, combine parsley, garlic, bay leaf, thyme, salt, bouillon cube and 1 cup boiling water. Pour over ribs and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Place ground beef, onion, peppers and celery in pan and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender and beef browned; drain.
While browning, cook macaroni; drain.
To the beef and peppers, add 1 cup tomato sauce, drained mushrooms and 1 can crushed tomatoes.
Stir.
Add in the macaroni.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and garlic powder to taste.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Spread gently in a 13 x 9-inch pan or 3 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy cream pie
directions: With mixer at low speed, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually blend in milk.
Add pudding mix and beat at low speed 2 minutes.
Fold in one cup Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break 1/2 the cake into small pieces in a punch bowl; add 1/2 the pudding, 1 can cherry pie filling and 1 can pineapple. Repeat.
Cover with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Sift together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Melt cheese and margarine.
Pour over sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased cookie sheet.
Let set to cool.
This will take a large mixing bowl.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Gradually add milk and other ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add coconut.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut.

title: french toasted ham and cheese
directions: Spread one side of bread with margarine; top each of four slices, margarine side up, with one slice of cheese, folded, and 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of bread (margarine side down).
Mix together eggs, cream and salt.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet or griddle over medium heat.
Quickly dip both sides of sandwich into mixture; shake off excess.
Saute in margarine for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Turn over and brown other side; use margarine as needed until all are done.
Garnish with avocado slices if desired.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Combine flour, sugar and yeast in large bowl.
Gradually add warm water to dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Cover with transparent wrap.
Let stand at least 2 days in warm place.

title: crispy baked potato slices
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Melt margarine, and crush corn flakes.
Dip potato slices into melted margarine and then into corn flake crumbs.
Arrange potatoes on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° until they test done when pierced with a fork.

title: fig bar
directions: Dough:
Add Crisco, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk and vanilla to form dough hard enough to roll.
Use pan 9 x 12-inches and layer with dough. Reserve enough dough for top layer.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, walnuts and margarine.
Press mixture into greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken nachos
directions: Assorted toppings:
tomatoes, sour cream, taco sauce, jalapeno peppers and lettuce.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken until it comes off bones.
Add rest of ingredients to broth, except the rivels.
Bring to a boil.
While waiting for boil, make rivels.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and	water;	let cool while cake bakes.
Add pop. Punch holes in cake and pour Jell-O over it.

title: crunchy mounds
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, stir together chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Stir in corn flakes and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: calabicita (little squash)
directions: Simmer first 5 ingredients until done. Drain.
Add butter and seasonings; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is brown. This one will surprise you, it's really different!

title: speedy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo. Let cool.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and dash of salt.
Beat and add vanilla.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 2 qt. Casserole. Mix all dry ingredients; beat in milk until lumps are gone. Pour batter into melted margarine. Do not stir! Spoon sliced peaches over top of batter. Do not stir! Bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees or until top is brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts; debone and put on bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixed vegetables over chicken.
Mix can of chicken soup with 2 cups broth.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix flour and milk.
Pour over for topping.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Remove all of the fat and gristle from the chicken.
Place in a container and pour the dressing over the chicken.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.
Grill, baste with remaining dressing while grilling.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and serve. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: kielbasa dip
directions: Cut up kielbasa into pieces and place in crock-pot.
Add jelly and chili sauce. Cook on low for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: turkey and bacon alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 4 min. of cooking time. Drain. In skillet mix soup, milk, cheese, turkey, pepper and fettuccine mixture and cook through, stirring often.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Heat oil to lightly brown garlic.
Add mushrooms, clams and a little salt and pepper and a cup of wine.
Also, add some butter and the spices you like.
Reduce and then add another cup of wine and the shrimp and cook until done.
Serve over linguine al dente.

title: kathy's brownies
directions: After boiling water, margarine and oil, add to sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix well.
Then add egg mixture.
Mix until well mixed.
Pour in cookie sheet sized pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: special k roast
directions: Blend together first six ingredients.
Add cereal and mix well.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. May be topped with cream of mushroom soup diluted 1/2 strength.

title: can't fail 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine marshmallows, evaporated milk, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil, then boil for 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat in chocolate chips until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix brown sugar, sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add the rest of ingredients to mix.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until fluffy. Add oil, egg, vanilla and almond; beat well. Combine dry ingredients; add to other mixture. Drop by teaspoons. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine remaining 3 ingredients together and add to pea mixture.
Stir to coat.
Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix the juice with the pudding.
Add Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Can be frozen.

title: cactus candy
directions: Select a small barrel cactus.
Remove spines and green outside layer with sharp knife.
Cut pulp across in slices 1 inch thick. Soak overnight in cold water.
Remove from water; cut into 1-inch cubes and cook in boiling water until tender.
Mix together the sugar, water and juices and add cactus.
Cook slowly until nearly all syrup is dissolved being careful not to scorch.
Remove cactus from syrup; drain and roll in powdered or granulated sugar.
For colored candy, add vegetable coloring.

title: ham 'n cheese roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Spread 1/4 mixture on one ham slice.
Repeat with remaining mixture and ham.
Roll up from short sides and chill for several hours.
To serve, slice ham rolls into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Arrange slices on top of crackers.

title: pecan bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder, blending until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Stir in pecans.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: marinated asparagus
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Place asparagus in a long dish (Tupperware works best) with top.
Remove spices.
Pour over asparagus.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: dandy's apple fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend eggs, milk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients all at once and mix just enough to moisten.
Stir in apple strips.
Drop into hot fat (375°) and fry until puffy and golden (3 to 4 minutes).
Turn once.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: steak strips
directions: Fry garlic until almost done.
Add meat and fry 2 minutes on first side, turn and sprinkle with Paul Prudhomme's seasoning. Cover with all vegetables.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes.
When vegetables have cooked down, add tomatoes.
Cook until hot.
Serve with rice.

title: banana cake "that's different"
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk and soda to bananas; add alternately with flour to cream mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into 3 pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy frozen salad
directions: Mix pie filling, Eagle Brand milk and pineapple together; fold in Cool Whip.
Pat ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: vanilla cookies(makes 100)
directions: In a large bowl blend dry ingredients except sugar.
In a separate bowl, cream together margarine and sugar, until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla to the sugar mixture and blend well. Next, add dry ingredients to the sugar mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Using a large scoop (#40) drop cookie dough on a greased baking sheet.
Cook at 325 degrees until light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Keep a close look.

title: quiche (kush)
directions: Brown
both
meats with veggies, except broccoli, until tender;
drain.
Cook
broccoli
separate until tender; drain. Mix meat mixture, add cheese and eggs.
Mix well all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie shells.	Bake until crusts are done.

title: easy spanish rice with beef casserole
directions: Bring water and beef bouillon to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan. Add rice; cover and lower heat to simmer.
Steam for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Put in large boiler and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and fold in zucchini and nuts.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake glass pans at 325° or 350° for metal pans for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove immediately.
Cool on rack and cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: minute fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter first then add other ingredients over low fire until all melts then boil 2 minutes. Remove from fire and beat until creamy and thick enough for frosting.

title: date and nut muffins
directions: Stir together water, oil, dates and vanilla.
In mixing bowl, combine flours, sugar, nuts and soda; add to date mixture.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Roll out each to make a little larger.
On crescent rolls add:
BBQ sauce, cooked chicken, shredded cheddar cheese, and onion if desired.
Fold up sides of crescent rolls.
Bake for specified time on crescent roll package.

title: white bean salad
directions: Drain beans (and rinse if you prefer), then place them in a large bowl.
Add salt, pepper, half the lemon juice and half the oil.
Mix gently with a fork and spoon.
Scoop the mixture into a serving platter lined with lettuce leaves.
Garnish rim of platter with parsley, reserving some to sprinkle lightly over beans. Place the tomato and onion slices in alternating rows on top of beans or in a circle design.
Sprinkle with remaining olive oil, lemon juice and reserved parsley.
Refrigerate for a
half hour before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and refrigerate.

title: three minute yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into whipped topping; mix thoroughly.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with fruit if desired.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight.
Take out of freezer 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Can be refroze.

title: old time homemade ice cream
directions: Scald the 1/2 gallon of milk.
Pour over eggs, condensed milk and sugar.
Add vanilla and pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. You may add sliced peaches, pineapple, bananas or nuts.

title: pork chops
directions: Put pork chops into casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over pork chops.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dijonnaise potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in potatoes, celery and onions; olives, too!
Cover and chill. Makes 6 cups.

title: microwave beef and mushroom ring
directions: Place water and butter in medium bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, at High power until boiling, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add stuffing mix; mix well.
Combine beef, eggs, chopped onion, bread crumbs, catsup, minced parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in second medium bowl; mix well.
Spread 1 can of mushrooms in even layer in bottom of 6-cup ring mold.
Cut medium onion crosswise into 1/8-inch thick slices; separate slices into rings.
Arrange onion rings in even layer over mushrooms.

title: chicken delight
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Lay 6 to 8 cooked chicken pieces on top.
Mix mayonnaise, chicken soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Put 1/2 to 1 cup shredded cheese on top of this mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Cook in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Bake covered 15 minutes in 425° oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken; top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
This is good served on top of spaghetti with additional spaghetti sauce poured over all.

title: asparagus with lemon
directions: Steam asparagus for 5 to 6 minutes or to your liking. Place in serving dish. In a large skillet, melt butter until slightly brown. Add lemon juice and garlic; stir and cook on low heat for 1 minute. Pour over asparagus and garnish with lemon wedges and almonds.

title: shrimp with vegetables and rice
directions: In a large pan, add rice, water, butter, onion soup, bouillon and mushrooms.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.
In separate pan, saute shrimp with garlic and parsley.
When rice is cooked, add in sauteed shrimp and mix.
Enjoy.

title: tomato soup(canning)
directions: Cook the tomatoes and run them through a colander to remove seeds.
Pressure cook the onions and celery and puree them in blender.
Add to tomato juice and cook for 20 minutes.
Also to tomato juice, add salt, pepper, sugar and oleo.
Make a thickening paste with a little bit of water and cornstarch; add to tomato mixture and cook 10 more minutes.
Put in jars and seal. Makes about 6 quarts.

title: sausage balls
directions: In crock-pot, put ketchup, vinegar, soy sauce, sugar and onion flakes.
Stir.
Mix in bowl the sausage, eggs and bread crumbs; shape into balls.
Brown in frying pan.
Add browned sausage balls to crock-pot.
Cook about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: wonder salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows.
Prepare remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: mama's divinity
directions: Cook to a firm ball (candy dropped in cold water).
Pour over 2 beaten egg whites that are beaten until stiff.
When adding syrup candy to egg whites, pour slowly over the egg whites so you cook them.
Be sure to use an electric mixer.
Beat until firm.
With 2 tablespoons, drop on wax paper.
Top with a pecan or maraschino cherry.
This can be colored with a few drops of cake color.

title: soy-oat waffles
directions: Soak soybeans overnight.
Combine in blender until foamy all ingredients.
(I prefer to use chop speed with 1/2 of the water on soaked beans until fine, then blend with the other ingredients.) Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
These waffles rise by steam, so take a little longer.
We prefer serving with fruit sauce.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Place in a casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, peanut butter and margarine until fluffy.
Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Combine oats, flour and soda.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press until 1/4-inch thick. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: chicken sausage gumbo
directions: Boil chicken until done in a large stock pot with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Let cool, bone and set aside. Brown sausage lightly and drain. Saute vegetables in oil or bacon drippings. To your large pot add rice, seasonings, chicken, gumbo mix, water, tomatoes, corn and gumbo file. After adding each ingredient, bring back to a boil prior to adding the next. When all has been added, simmer for a minimum of 25 minutes. This will allow rice to cook.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in saucepan.
Blend in peanut butter. Add cereal.
Toss to coat. Coat with powdered sugar. Yields 3 pounds.

title: red cabbage with apples(rotkohl mit apleln)
directions: Wash cabbage under cold running water and remove tough outer leaves; cut into quarters.
To shred cabbage, cut quarters crosswise into 1/2-inch strips.
Put cabbage in large mixing bowl and sprinkle with vinegar, sugar and salt, then toss about to coat evenly with the mixture.

title: mary jane's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil frozen broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes or cook fresh broccoli.
Mix together eggs, mayonnaise, soup and onion. Mix well.
Add cheese and the broccoli.
Turn into 2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle top with Ritz crackers.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips in 2-quart pan over hot water until melted.
Stir in peanuts and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.
Store in tight container.

title: food and wine's hazelnut chunk cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread nuts on baking tray and bake until fragrant, 6 to 8 minutes.
Place nuts in a dish towel and rub to remove some of the skin.
Coarsely chop and set aside.

title: apple a la mode dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl of food processor and process until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Great with fresh fruit or small cubes of pound cake.

title: peach shake(lo-cal)
directions: If using fresh peaches, immerse them in a pot of boiling water and blanch until their skins start to split, about 1 minute. Immediately drain the peaches and cool them under cold running water.
Peel off the skins and slice.
Place the peaches, raspberries, milk, lemon juice, honey, vanilla and cinnamon in a blender.
Process until smooth, 20 to 30 seconds.
Pour into 4 glasses.

title: one-step pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch (12-cup) Bundt or tube pan.
Beat together butter, sugar, flour, baking powder, yogurt, eggs and vanilla, at low speed in a large bowl, until well blended.
Increase speed to medium; beat 3 minutes. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad carbonara
directions: Bring mushrooms with broth to a boil in a 10-inch skillet. Add peas, cover and cook 3 minutes.
Uncover and add ham.
Heat and stir until broth is absorbed and peas are tender-crisp.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs.
Put in baking pan.
Top with buttered soft bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: georgia peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into greased muffin tins; fill 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes or until muffins test done.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cover strips of venison completely with sauce.
Soak meat for 6 to 8 hours in sauce in glass bowl.
Put foil in bottom of stove, hang strips on oven racks on toothpicks.
Push the toothpicks through one end.
Heat oven to 170° or 200°, leave them for 4 hours.

title: granola candy bars(makes about 24 bars)
directions: In a large bowl microwave chips on 50% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until well melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Press into buttered 2-quart rectangular casserole dish.
(You can press additional crushed cereal over the top for garnish, if you like.) Chill and cut into bars.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage and onion together; crumble until fine.
Add cheese; melt slowly.
Add tomatoes.
This can be frozen.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix well. Add grated carrots and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until cake tests done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Cream in shortening.
Add eggs.
Beat (stir) until well blended.
Blend in nuts and bananas; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: bayfield eggs
directions: Fry sausage and drain well; grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break eggs into pan and poke the yolks.
Top eggs with all of the sausage, 1/2 of the cheese and all of the onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Cover all with the cream and the remainder of the cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth (by hand or with beaters).
Mix in taco seasoning.
Spread mixture in casserole or pan.
Top with salsa or sauce, chopped lettuce, tomatoes (optional) and shredded cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to oil mixture.
Stir in vanilla, apples, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Spoon batter into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 2 bread pans. Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, zucchini and water; mix well. Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and vanilla. Add nuts, if desired. Bake for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool completely.

title: peanut butter pralines
directions: Mix the buttermilk, butter and sugar in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.

Add peanuts and cook over medium heat to soft ball stage or to 234° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Add soda, vanilla and peanut butter. Stir rapidly only until mixture is creamy and thickened. Drop rapidly from a tablespoon onto a lightly greased baking sheet to form patties.
Let stand until cool and set.

title: spanish hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer until thickened.
(This can be thickened in a crock-pot.)

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Combine raisins, carrots and drained pineapple.
Blend in mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Serve on crisp salad greens. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: rolls *
directions: Mix salt, Crisco and sugar with boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or until needed (will keep for a week).

title: venison roast
directions: Roast venison until tender.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients except flour and pour over venison in plastic or stainless steel container.
Let marinate for 24 hours, mixing occasionally.
Thicken with flour and water mixture and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: gena's lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Bring to boil, then cut off heat.
Mix the remaining ingredients in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put 1 cup of meat-sauce mixture.
Cover mixture with a layer of uncooked lasagna.
Pour 1/2 the cheese mixture, another layer of noodles and all the sauce.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: fried pike and tomatoes
directions: Dip fillets in mixture of flour, tarragon, salt and pepper. Heat butter in a large skillet and fry fillets until golden.
Turn and move to the side of the skillet.
Put tomatoes in skillet and sprinkle fish with the capers.
Cook until tomatoes are hot and fish is flaky.

title: hominy grits souffle
directions: Mix water, grits and salt and cook about 5 minutes or until thick.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake one hour at 350°. Last 15 minutes, sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and paprika.

title: blueberry oat muffins
directions: In bowl, combine oats and milk; let stand a few minutes.
In another bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir egg and butter into oat mixture. Add oat mixture all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries; fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: lemon party meringue pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, 2/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup of the water in saucepan.
Blend in egg yolks and remaining water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full, bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in lemon juice and butter.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy throughout.
Gradually beat in 6 tablespoons of sugar and continue beating until mixture will form stiff, shiny peaks. Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes or until meringue is delicately browned.
Cool at least 4 hours before cutting.

title: apple bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the buttermilk, oil, egg whites and honey in a small bowl.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, bran, milk powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add buttermilk mixture and stir until moistened. Gently stir in the chopped apple and raisins.
Spray twelve 2 1/2-inch diameter muffin-pan cups with nonstick cooking spray. Fill each with an equal amount of batter.
Bake for 25 minutes (until muffins are golden brown and a toothpick, inserted in center, comes out dry).
Cool muffins in pan for 5 minutes, then transfer to wire rack until completely cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, onion, eggs, salt and pepper and pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and egg well.
Save 1 cup for top; press remaining in cake pan.

title: deep dish cheddar chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
If you are using boneless chicken, melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch glass or metal pan while oven is preheating.
Roll chicken in melted margarine and cook for 10 minutes on each side.
Saute onion in a small pan.

title: microwave cheese sticks
directions: Cream butter and cheese together; mix in other ingredients. Pour onto well floured surface and roll out to about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out thin strips and lay on waxed paper or paper towels. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: sprouts with sour cream
directions: Cut sprouts in one-inch pieces; rinse well and place in pan with 1-inch of water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, in another saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, brown sugar, salt and mustard until blended.
Gradually stir in milk; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Reduce heat; stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Drain the sprouts; place in a serving bowl.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring cherries, sugar and water to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: cream cheese & olive pinwheel sandwiches
directions: Place 4 slices of trimmed bread in a vertical line, overlap adjoining ends, flatten with a rolling pin and crimp touching ends together.
Spread cream cheese on all slices.
Place about 5 olives on the end of bottom piece.
Roll up bread.
Wrap rolls in foil and slice when cold.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix and bring mixture to a boil; pour over vegetables. Do not stir. Refrigerate about 24 hours. Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: easy date nut bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Make a well and add in order, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Turn into greased shallow dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches).
Cut into bars while warm.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Great for the holidays.

title: tri-level brownies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then add the rest.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Simmer all of ingredients 1 hour.
Add 1 cup diced potatoes and 1/2 bell pepper, chopped.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes until potatoes are done.
Seasonings may be adjusted to personal taste.

title: pasta salad
directions: Add all ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour to allow flavors to mix.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Brush pork chops on both sides with mustard.
Brown lightly in frying pan.
Layer pork chops with soup, onion and celery in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until cooked.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt sugar in skillet over low heat; stir with wooden spoon. Stir in nuts when sugar becomes light brown syrup.
Carefully pour into greased shallow pan.
Mark squares while candy is still warm. Cool completely; break into squares or irregular pieces, if you wish.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; place in crock-pot with cheese/salsa and cook until cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: grandma's brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add milk.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7 minutes on greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: squash pickle
directions: Place squash, onion, pepper and salt in large pan.
Cover with ice cubes.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over squash, onion and pepper.
Bring to a good boil.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into two 8-inch pie pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
It makes it's own crust.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer 1:
Mix together lettuce, onion and green onion.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, syrup and butter or margarine. Add pecan halves. Pour into a 9-inch shallow unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between the center and edge comes out clean. Cool before serving.

title: favorite carrot cake
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Drain the pineapple and add the juice to the dry ingredients mixture along with eggs, oil and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, nuts, carrots and raisins.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients; pour over bread slices.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake in a 325° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread; let cool.
Crumble a layer in a dish.
Follow with a layer of the first 5 ingredients.
Make a total of 3 layers.

title: light brownies
directions: Melt butter and blend in brown sugar; add eggs and beat well. Let cool.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes (approximately). When done, may sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fireside cheese spread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cheese spread, cream cheese, butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Blend thoroughly. Chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: hildy's hot seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and fennel
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet and brown chicken.
Remove to baking dish.
In same skillet, saute onion, garlic, mushrooms and fennel until onions are golden.
Don't brown them.
Stir to keep from burning.
Remove from heat; add yogurt and blend, scraping browned bits from bottom of skillet.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes to brown.

title: poultry casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute pepper and onion in oil.
Mix all ingredients together and put in baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kris kringles
directions: Melt butter or margarine and marshmallows.
Stir in food coloring and vanilla.
Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by teaspoonful on buttered wax paper.
Decorate with red hots.

title: scott's favorite potato salad
directions: While potatoes are still warm, sprinkle with a little vinegar or Italian dressing or pickle brine.
Set aside.
Mix onion, celery, parsley, radishes and peppers with mayonnaise.
If olives are desired, use about 8 each, more or less to taste.
Add salt, celery seed and fresh ground pepper, but remember that the potatoes have vinegar on them, so be careful in adding salt.

title: saucy skillet supper
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In large skillet, cook ground beef, celery and onion.
Drain fat. Add tomatoes (breaking up with spoon), tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cooked macaroni with meat sauce; heat on low for 5 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in grated cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat pies fathiyir bi lahm
directions: Fry meat, onions, nuts and seasonings.
Cool.
Then add labnee. Roll ball of dough into a circular shape.
Put heaping tablespoonful of filling in the center.
Close in a triangular shape.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly brown.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: *Can be substituted with 1 cup applesauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pecans in crust first.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and flavoring.
Start cake in cold oven at 250° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix rice, sugar, pineapple and vanilla. Stir in cherries and marshmallows. Fold whipping cream into mixture.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, dry milk, baking powder and salt in bowl. Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Bake 18 minutes in mini muffin pan at 350°.

title: orange-pineapple punch
directions: In a large punch bowl combine first three ingredients. Refrigerate if making ahead of time.
Just before serving, gradually add ginger ale.
Stir.
Top with scoops of sherbet, orange slices and mint leaves.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: super-fast chicken parmesan
directions: In a pie plate or on a sheet of waxed paper, combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Rinse chicken; pat dry. Brush chicken with milk.
Coat with crumb mixture.
Spray a cold large skillet with nonstick spray coating.
Preheat skillet, then add chicken.
Cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink, turning the pieces occasionally to brown evenly.
Transfer to a platter; cover to keep warm.
Wipe skillet with paper towels.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes and soak in cold water 12 hours.
Pat dry and grate into a small bowl.
Add egg yolks, baking powder, salt and flour.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks and fold into mixture.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into hot greased griddle or skillet.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, including orange slices. Beat eggs in separate bowl and mix with dry ingredients.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil and add 2 cups sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer to desired consistency.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream
butter
and sugars; add vanilla, then eggs.
Mix dry ingredients
and
add
to
batter.
Chill dough.
To make "real" buffalo chips, each cookie should be made from 1/4 cup cookie dough, or they can be made in smaller version.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: georgia pecan drop cakes(this is an old recipe)
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Cream butter and sugar, adding beaten eggs and other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Leave room for them to spread.
Bake at 350° until set and lightly browned.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion, garlic and carrot; cook slightly.
Add soup, cheese and oregano.
Mix together and pour into a 9-inch pie plate with crust.
Cover with crust; make slit for steam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until crust is browned.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Stir cold water, bananas, marshmallows and pineapple into gelatin.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 dish coated with cooking spray; refrigerate until firm. Meanwhile, in a saucepan, combine sugar and flour.	Stir in reserved pineapple juice until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of hot filling into egg; return all to the pan, stirring constantly.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth; add cooled filling.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over gelatin (dish will be full). Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Pour everything in bowl.
Blend well except chocolate chips. Blend chocolate chips last.
Spray Pam in Bundt pan.
Add cake mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: libby's mushroom deluxe casserole
directions: Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish half of mushrooms with juice, half of stuffing and half of cheese.
Repeat layers. Pour half and half over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheery cherry bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, measure, then sift with baking powder and salt.
Add nuts and cherries.
Alternately add flour and cherry juice (mix green and red cherries for Christmas bread).
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 1-pound loaf pan.

title: veal piccata
directions: Place cutlets between two sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/8-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge cutlets in flour mixture. Cook in oil in a skillet over medium heat 1 minute on each side. Remove from skillet, keep warm.
Add vermouth to skillet.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add butter and lemon juice.
Heat until butter melts.
Pour over cutlets and sprinkle with lemon rind.

title: buns and rolls
directions: Beat with electric mixer, then add 2 1/2 cups more flour; beat with spoon.
Let rise until doubled.
Pinch off in small rolls for buns or rolls.
Can also be used for cinnamon rolls.
Roll dough out; spread with oleo, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut off in 2-inch slices and place in well greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cheese.
Grease a 10 1/2-inch skillet and place in an oven to heat.
Pour half the mixture into hot skillet and sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Add remaining mixture on top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: a berry good shake
directions: Puree until thick and smooth.

title: fruit salad
directions: Take juice from can of chunk pineapple and enough peach juice to make 1 cup juice.
Mix juice with vanilla pudding.
Add pineapple chunks, peaches (chopped up), banana, coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix altogether and chill in refrigerator at least one hour.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken quiche(6 main dish servings)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle chicken, cheese and onion in pastry.
In a bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients and beat slightly.
Pour into pastry shell over cheese and chicken. Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes more or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: creamed chicken(50 generous servings)
directions: Steam chicken, take off bones.
Saute onions, celery, peppers and carrots in small amount of oil.
Mix scalded milk with 2 to 3 quarts chicken broth.
Add cornstarch and water to liquids, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
When thickened, add sauteed vegetables and chicken pieces.
Add pimiento.
Taste (chicken bouillon granules can be added if needed for flavor).

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: mexican corn bread casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion in skillet until done.
Mix corn bread mix, eggs, milk, peppers and 1/2 can of corn.
Layer, as follows, in a greased 9-inch casserole:
1/2 corn bread mixture, then meat and onion, cheese, 1/2 (the remaining) corn and then the remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad cake
directions: DO NOT USE MIXER!!

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Place bacon in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with paper towels. Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon. Reserve drippings in pie plate.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and
dice red peppers and onions.
Put in a large pot to
cook.
Add
rest
of	ingredients and cook all together until thick.
Can while hot.
Makes about 12 pints.

title: potato pie
directions: While the quartered potatoes are cooking:
Saute onions, peppers, celery, garlic and mushrooms in small amount of oil for 10 minutes.
Add shredded carrots and cook for 2 or 3 more minutes.
Mash cooked potatoes with butter.
Add spices and sesame seed and mix well.
In an oiled 9-inch pie plate or shallow casserole, press in the mashed potato mixture (like a pie crust). Sprinkle with 1/2 the grated cheese and the alfalfa sprouts over the potatoes.
Add sauteed vegetables.
Place sliced tomatoes in a circle around the dish.
Sprinkle last half of grated cheese over tomatoes.
Top with a handful of fresh parsley.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese melts and potato forms light crust (about 45 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Mix ingredients well.
Make dough in walnut sized balls and bake 25 minutes.
Cool for about 10 minutes and roll in powdered sugar.
Will keep well in covered container.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, butter and corn.
Season well.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat a 13 x 9 baking dish with cooking spray.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Start in a slow 250° oven.
Increase to 350° after filling sets around the edge.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate truffle trifle(needs to be refrigerated for at least 6 hours before serving.)
directions: Day or two before serving, cook cake and pudding according to directions and refrigerate.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Stir into first mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows melt (about 10 minutes).

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Combine 8 tablespoons butter, the egg yolk, sugar, flour and salt in a bowl.
When completely blended, add chocolate chunks. Divide the dough in half and roll each one into a cylinder about 1 1/2-inches in diameter and 6-inches long.
Refrigerate until hard, about 2 hours.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, melted butter and syrup.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between the outside and center comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, put in casserole dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peg's chicken croquettes
directions: Cook chicken and shred. Saute onions and celery in butter until tender; add to chicken.
Also add bread crumbs, soup and enough flour to form into 1 1/2-inch croquette balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs.
Fry in deep oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Drain on paper towel. Serve hot with sauce.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage, slice onions and crumble noodles from soup. Add toasted almonds.
Mix all together in large bowl.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with 1/2 c sugar.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place butter in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and place in oven to melt.
Make batter using remaining 3/4 c sugar, flour, milk. Blend until smooth.
When butter is melted, pour batter evenly over butter.
DO NOT STIR.
Add fruit to mixture and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is slightly brown and crusty.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Servings: 6 to 8.

title: cream of potato and onion soup
directions: Cook potatoes in a quart of water until well done.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Mash potatoes.
Saute onions and celery in butter until light brown.
Sift in flour, stirring until blended. Slowly add the potato water and cook until thick.
Mix the potatoes with the evaporated milk and water; add to the soup.
Add seasonings and heat through.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat in pumpkin, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour batter into greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into the center comes out clean. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Take chicken out of water and put spaghetti in to cook.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces and set aside.
Drain spaghetti when done and add soup, approximately 6 ounces of grated cheese and the chicken to the spaghetti.
Mix and put in a 13 x 9-inch dish and put the rest of the cheese on top.
Warm in the oven until cheese melts.

title: artichoke pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: blueberry angel food cake roll(fat-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 2 jelly roll pans with aluminum foil.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Divide into lined pans.
Spread evenly with spatula, removing air bubbles.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: asparagus-english pea casserole
directions: Combine asparagus, peas, eggs and soup.
Place in casserole dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
In bowl mix flour, salt and cocoa.
In another bowl mix buttermilk and soda.
To oil mixture add eggs and vinegar, then alternately add flour and milk to mixture.
Add vanilla and coloring.
Bake at 325°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix
together
sugar,
flour, eggs and cocoa.
Then mix together the margarine, evaporated milk, vanilla flavoring and salt.
Add	this
mixture
to the sugar and flour mixture; mix well.
In the crusts, put layer of coconut and chopped pecans. Pour the
other
mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: original french potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes.
Boil in salted water for 3 minutes and drain. Mix onion, flour, olive oil, parsley, nutmeg and lemon rind.
Add potatoes
and
mix until potatoes are well coated. Place in
a buttered baking dish.
Drizzle more oil on top, if desired.
Bake at	450°
for 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned
and tender.
Pour
lemon
juice
over
top
of baked potatoes and serve.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix the pudding with the milk; fold in the Cool Whip and set aside.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with crackers, pudding, crackers, pudding, crackers and end with crackers on top.
Spread with icing and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: spiced cocoa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
To make hot cocoa, use 1 to 2 tablespoons spiced cocoa mix per cup of hot milk.
Serve hot or iced.
Makes 1 1/2 cups mix.
Serves about 18.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown beef and sausage together in a large skillet.
When brown, add pepperoni, then green
pepper, mushrooms and seasonings to taste (do not add sugar to meat).
Drain.
Cook macaroni in oil and water.
Drain (just a little oil to keep from sticking).
Mix together macaroni and meat mixture with all other ingredients, including sugar, reserving 1 package of Mozzarella cheese.
Season again to taste.
Place in large roasting pan.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and more Parmesan .
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma's hot dish
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: chicken crescent casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and cook until hot and bubbly. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with crescent rolls. Top with cheese, almonds and margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in hot oil until tender.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots; mix well. Add zucchini and onion mixture to cream mixture and mix well.
In a separate bowl, mix melted butter with stuffing mix.

title: chicken l'orange
directions: Saute chicken in margarine 8 to 10 minutes, remove and set aside.
Mix cornstarch and juice.
Stir in 57 sauce and marmalade. Pour into skillet; heat, stirring until thick.
Place chicken in sauce, heat and serve.

title: my friend's grandmother's no fail pie crust recipe
directions: Cut the shortening into the flour with a pastry blender. Sprinkle with salt.
Add cold water, little by little, mixing it in with a fork or with fingers until fully blended into the dough. Divide into 2 balls.
Roll each ball on flour and roll out on a board, creating a crust that fits the size of the pan.
Lay the crust at the bottom of the pie pan; trim to size.
Roll out the other ball of dough to make a crust to cover the pie.

title: bean dish
directions: Mix ingredients (except cornstarch) into crock-pot.
Cook at least 5 to 6 hours on low setting.
Add cornstarch and mix before serving.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix pie filling and cherries in ungreased square baking dish (8 x 8-inch).
Spread evenly.
Mix Bisquick, nuts, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake until brown, about 35 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and drain. Mix meat, cheese, soup and rotel in crockpot. Stir until cheese melts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding according to directions on the box. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Smash Oreos. Using 1/2 of each mixture, put 1 layer of Oreos, 1 layer cream cheese mixture, 1 layer pudding, 1 layer cream cheese, 1 layer pudding, top with the rest of the Oreos.

title: forgottens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip the egg whites.
Add the sugar; whip until stiff.
Fold in the chocolate chips and pecans.
Place on foiled cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Place in oven overnight. Turn off oven.
Do not peek.

title: creamy pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut each tenderloin into 8 pieces. Place each piece between 2 pieces of waxed paper and flatten to 3/4-inch thickness.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Put into a loaf pan. Cover with bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well done.

title: aunt gladie's fudge
directions: Bring to boil sugar, evaporated milk and salt.
Boil 6 minutes after it comes to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Break chocolate bars and chips into sugar mixture.
Add marshmallow cream, chopped nuts and butter.
Pour into buttered pans and let cool.
Very rich.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Mix together sugar and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Makes 7 cups.
Serve with gingersnaps. Can serve in hollowed out small pumpkins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in double boiler top.
Cook over boiling water, stirring 15 to 20 minutes, or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Press into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch squares. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Slowly cook hamburger, sausage and onion in frying pan until crumbles.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot and cook several hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Mix tomato sauce, garlic powder and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese. Spread sauce on top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sauce; arrange vegetables on top, then sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese.
