Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in graham cracker crust.
Store in freezer overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs. Add the sugar, beating until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in the corn syrup, pecan halves and vanilla extract.
Pour into pie shell. Place on middle shelf of oven. After 10 minutes, reduce oven temperature to 325° and continue baking for about 35 minutes or until filling is set and crust is lightly browned.

title: beef chimichangas
directions: Brown beef
stew
meat	in
a little oil in Dutch oven. Add water,
garlic,
chili
powder,
oregano,
salt, cumin and pepper and simmer for at
least
2 hours (the longer it cooks, the easier it is to
shred later) or until remaining liquid is absorbed. Shred meat with 2
forks or let cool and pull apart with fingers.

title: mini tacos
directions: Cut each tortilla with 2 1/2-inch cutter into 3 rounds, making 4 dozen mini tortillas.
(Reserve scraps on shallow buttered baking sheet, sprinkle with seasoned salt, barbecue spice or your favorite herb and bake in hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until toasted.
Cool, then store in airtight container and use as nibblers.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water. Break up cranberry sauce and add to jello mixture. Stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple and nuts, then refrigerate.

title: chocolate glaze(good for devil's food cake in tube pan)
directions: Dissolve cocoa in 1 tablespoon hot water.
Add oil and blend sugar and 1 tablespoon hot water.
Pour over cake.
(Can use more sugar or water, if needed.)

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Arrange sliced potatoes on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the uncooked hamburger next and top with the onion rings.
Add the beans and their liquid.
Top with the tomato soup; spread evenly.
Scatter bacon pieces on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. During the last 15 minutes, place cheese on the top to melt. Serve with green salad, breadsticks and a cup of fruit.

title: poppy seed rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar into very warm water and stir until dissolved.
Mix scalded milk, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and margarine until all is melted and dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Cut the tomatoes into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Salt and pepper both sides of slices.
Dredge in flour, coating well and shaking off excess.
Heat butter until foamy, but not browned.
Cook tomatoes gently until first side is lightly browned.
Before turning, crumble 1 tablespoon brown sugar over the tops.
Turn. Add extra butter if needed.
Crumble remaining sugar over tomatoes. Fry second sides until lightly browned.
Remove tomatoes.
Hard green tomatoes will have to be cooked 5 to 10 minutes.
Can use bacon fat.

title: spicy hermits
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Add this mixture, alternating with milk and molasses.
Finally add raisins.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with sugar.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix and cook at 350° about 3 hours.
Can be cooked in crock-pot all night on low.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: norine's pheasant casserole
directions: Disjoint pheasant and marinate in wine for 3 hours.
Add spices.
Brown meat in butter in a hot iron skillet, turning often. Combine mushroom soup, cream, sour cream and onion; cook over low heat.
Add 1/2 cup wine and mushrooms.
Combine with meat and bake at 275° for 1 hour.
This is also excellent using wild duck.

title: bachlorette bean soup
directions: Open can of soup, pour into saucepan, fill can with water, pour into saucepan, put pan on stove, turn the burner on and put pan on burner.
Stir occasionally.
Let soup boil.
When soup boils for 5 minutes, soup is done.
Remove from burner, turn off burner.
Pour some soup into a bowl and serve with a bologna and cheese sandwich.

title: goolosh
directions: Cook macaroni; brown chuck and mix tomato sauce, spatini and garlic sauce with chuck.
Mix with macaroni and top with cheese; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oven steak supper
directions: Place meat in center of large piece of aluminum foil. Sprinkle meat with soup mix; cover with vegetables; dot with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Fold foil and seal securely to hold juices.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 450° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mel's no bake banana pudding
directions: Blend vanilla pudding and
milk until smooth. Stir in sour cream and fold in Cool Whip.
Place a layer of broken wafers into dish of your choice. Cover wafers with layer of sliced bananas. Top this layer with pudding mix.
Layer in this order to top, ending with pudding mix. Sprinkle top with crushed wafers.
Let stand 4 hours or more in refrigerator before serving.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender, about an hour.
Remove skin; pick chicken from bones.
Put chicken in a baking dish (use 13 x 7-inch dish).
Melt margarine; pour over chicken.
Sift flour and salt; blend in milk until smooth.
Spread flour mixture over chicken.
In saucepan, blend soup and broth.
Heat to boiling; pour over flour mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven until brown.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: krispie datelets
directions: Melt butter and sugar over low heat.
Add egg, dates and vanilla.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring frequently, then stir in Rice Krispies and chopped pecans.
Allow mixture to cool enough to handle.
Roll into balls and then roll the balls in coconut to cover them.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender.
Skin in cold water.
Slice and put back in pot.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over beets. Heat to a simmer and let simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars and seal tight.

title: turkey or chicken sausage
directions: Blend together all dry ingredients.
Add water and onion and again blend.
Add turkey or chicken and mix together thoroughly. Allow to marinate in refrigerator for an hour or two.
Shape into patties.
Coat with flour. Saut in olive oil about 10 minutes. Turn over and continue to cook another 10 minutes.
When done, add a few tablespoons water to pan to deglaze.
Allow sausage to sit in liquid until it is mostly absorbed.

title: steak roll-ups
directions: Judge amounts needed by number of people you are feeding. Melt some butter in skillet.
Tear up sandwich steak and brown in melted butter.
Roll out thawed bread on very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread steak, spaghetti sauce, cheese and mushrooms over bread.
Roll bread from wide end and bake according to bread directions.
Slice and serve.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in quarters.
Place in steamer (microwavable) over water with lid on for 5 minutes.
Remove; place in microwavable dish.
Add butter and cheese.
Microwave 5 more minutes.

title: date-nut bread
directions: In medium saucepan, combine dates, water, butter and vanilla. Cook 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add egg and sugar.
Sift flour with remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Put in a greased and wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 1 hour or until done.
Cool.
Frost and decorate with nuts and candied cherries.
Keeps well.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese in a bowl until creamy.
Add peanut butter and sugar and beat until creamy.
Add milk and stir in cool whip. Pour this in your pie crust.
If you want to serve within the next two hours after preparation, place in the freezer.
However, if you make it ahead of time for the next day, you can chill it in the fridge.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs together. Add pumpkin and water. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add to pumpkin mixture. Mix well and add vanilla, pecans and dates. Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans and fill halfway. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Allow to cool before removing from cans.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Sift 4 cups flour over all fruit.
Mix with your hands.
Cream together sugar and butter or margarine.
Cream thoroughly.
Add well beaten eggs.
Mix butter mixture with fruit mixture with your hands.
Pour over lemon extract.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Oil loaf pans and line bottom with oiled brown paper.
Bake at 300° for 1 3/4 to 2 hours.

title: oat bran fruit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tins with paper liners. In large bowl, mix oat bran, flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and dried fruits.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, buttermilk, honey, eggs and oil.
Make a well in dry ingredients. Pour liquid mixture into well and stir gently.
Do not overmix. Spoon into paper lined muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onions in saucepan.
Mix everything together and put in casserole plate.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot beef and rice dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain grease from skillet.
Add Ro-Tel, chili beans, taco seasoning and cooked rice. Simmer 10 minutes with lid on pan.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with chips and then cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: jello delight
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and let come to a boil.
Pour over Jell-O and let chill enough to be mushy.
Add pineapple to other ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove all skin from the chicken, rinse and dry the pieces thoroughly.
Season, coat each piece with oil or dip in milk, shake to remove excess and roll in the crumbs. Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken in an oiled baking pan.
(Line pan with foil for easy clean up.)
Bake for 45 minutes or more.
Crumbs will form a crisp "skin".
Yield: 4 servings.
Approximate calories per serving are 270.
This does not hav a cornflake taste.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pour off dark water accumulated on top of grated potatoes. Add all ingredients and beat well.
With spoon, drop mixture on hot griddle.
Fry on both sides.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cheese on bottom of dish.
Brown ground beef and mix in a jar of taco sauce.
Pour meat over cream cheese.
Top with Cheddar.
Heat in microwave until Cheddar melts.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg and press down in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour.
Add the buttermilk, flavoring and coconut.
Cook 1 hour at 325° to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pork chop dinner
directions: Pour a little of the soup, undiluted, in the bottom of a baking dish; place the pork chops over soup in a single layer. Pour remaining soup over the top. Layer onions on top of pork chops and seal baking dish with foil. Poke a couple of air holes in the foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: pepperoni roll
directions: Roll bread out on table.
Fill with remaining ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add soup mix and chicken.
Bring back to a boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered 12 - 15 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles.
In a large skillet, brown beef.
Remove beef and drain fat.
In the same skillet, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, noodles and soups.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
except 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on

title: stuffed celery
directions: Blend in blender container until smooth.
Spread on celery stalks and chill before serving.

title: the sherry cake
directions: Beat mixture for 5 minutes on medium speed.
Pour it into a greased tube cake pan or mold and bake it for 45 minutes at 350°. Dust with powdered sugar and fill center with fresh or frozen strawberries.

title: cheese, bacon and tomato pie
directions: Mix onion and flour; pour int pie shell.
Add tomato slices and sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 400° until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with shredded lettuce at time of serving.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually; beat well.
Melt margarine and add cocoa.
Stir cocoa mixture into eggs and sugar. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan. Place this pan in a larger pan which has hot water in it.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: lulu's pound cake
directions: In large bowl, soften margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Add milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together; mix well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; blend mixture well after each egg.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for about 3 minutes.
Squash should be crisp.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, squash and onion.
Add salt to taste. Combine stuffing mix with melted oleo.
Spread half the stuffing mix in the bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top of stuffing.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: jaegerschnitzel
directions: Using a mallet or meat tenderizer, pound each cutlet until it is 1/4-inch thick.
Beat the eggs and combine with the milk.
Dip each cutlet into the egg mixture.
Coat generously with crumbs.

title: saucy barbecued franks
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Simmer over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm with toothpicks.
Use electric fry-pan or chafing dish to keep warm.
This is an appetizer.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer at least one hour. Serve over pasta.

title: butterscotch fondue
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, syrup and 4 tablespoons water.
Bring to boil.
Stir in milk; simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches thread stage (230°) this does not have to be precise.
Add vanilla and pour into fondue pot or dish for buffet table.
More water can be added if it thickens.

title: nanny ruby's banana nut bread
directions: Mix together soda, salt and flour.
Cream together butter and sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well, adding nuts during mixing.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: busy woman's dream casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Place in bottom of a 10 x 10-inch casserole.
Spread soup over ground chuck.
Place Tater Tots on top and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's dressing(hand me down recipe)
directions: The mixture should be mushy; if it isn't add a bit more broth. Saute the onion and celery until the onion is translucent and mush all ingredients together in large pot (using your hands, clean of course).
Grease and flour a big, deep sheet pan.
Pour mixture in or stuff your bird.
You can tell when it's done; a great deal of the moisture will be gone.
It should be semi-dry.

title: tomato soup
directions: Chop the tomatoes, making sure to keep the juice.
Chop the onion and celery and grate the carrot.
Saute the onion, celery and carrot in the oil until the onion is soft.
In a stock pot, place the tomatoes, celery, carrot and onion; add the seasonings and simmer gently for 15 minutes.
If you would like a creamy texture, puree the vegetables in a blender or food processor. Return liquid to stock pot, adding the hot vegetable stock and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
For a thicker soup, use only 2 or 3 cups of stock and reduce seasonings.
Makes 8 cups.

title: moist bread stuffing
directions: Saute, until tender, onions and celery in margarine.
Add parsley, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Stir well until thoroughly mixed.
Mix with bread cubes and eggs.
Mix well.
Make 1 cup stuffing per pound of bird.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix the pie pastry
and roll out and line the pie plate with pastry.
Slice
peeled
tomatoes into the shell, sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon
and
nutmeg
over the tomatoes.
Add the butter, cover with top
crust.
Bake
in
hot
oven at 400° at least 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: catsup
directions: Cook ingredients together for 1 hour, uncovered.
Press through colander and put to boil.
Add 5 tablespoons cornstarch or Clear Jell mixed with 1 cup vinegar.
Stir constantly and boil for 10 minutes.
Bottle or seal.

title: berryless raspberry jam
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups water in blender.
Add green tomatoes so that when blended will make 4 1/2 cups.
Use only green tomatoes with no hint of pink.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. Add 2 cups sugar and boil 10 minutes more.
Skim foam off top. Remove from heat and quickly stir in raspberry jello.
Pour into container and cover with paraffin and lids or refrigerate.
Any flavored jello can be used.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: In large saucepan combine first 6 ingredients; bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 12-14 minutes or till vegies are tender.
Meanwhile in another saucepan melt butter, stir in flour till smooth, gradually add milk; bring to a boil cook and stir 2 minutes or till thickened.
Stir into veggie mixture.
Heat through, sprinkle with cheese in bowl.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well and serve with potato chips.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and press evenly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onion.
Let set 2 hours in salt.
Drain juice off.
Don't wash.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 cup white vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let set 1 hour.
Pack in freezer boxes and freeze.

title: confetti ice cream punch
directions: Mix fruit punch with strawberries and ice cream when ready
to serve.
If an ice ring is desired, put some punch and strawberries into jello mold and freeze, then add to punch just before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in oblong baking dish.
Add remaining tomato sauce on top of meat loaf.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Spread 1/2 of wafer crumbs in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown, but still soft (12 to 15 minutes).

title: blue slime sipper
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine Jello and boiling water. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
To serve, stir Jello with a large spoon until it is broken into small pieces.
Place 1/4 cup of lemonade in a large, clear tumbler.
Add 1/2 cup of Jello to the lemonade. Add 1/2 cup Sprite.
Stir slightly and you are ready to slurp up some slime.

title: libby's cranberry-pumpkin bread
directions: Combine
eggs,	 sugar,
oil
and
pumpkin;
mix
well. Combine flour, pie	spice, soda and salt in a large bowl; make well in center.
Pour
pumpkin
mixture
into
well; stir just until dry
ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon
batter
into	2
greased and floured 8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch
aluminum	loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1
hour
or
until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 2 loaves.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until almost tender, about 20 minutes. Drain and brush with fat.
Combine crumbs, paprika and salt. Roll greased potatoes in this mixture until well covered.
Bake in greased shallow pan in a 425° oven until well browned and tender. About 10 minutes.

title: christmas breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch dish with crescent rolls, pushing dough up sides of pan.
Blend sauteed sausage, cheese and 3 eggs together. Pour in sausage mixture; cover with second can of crescent rolls. Brush top of rolls with 1 egg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Make a day ahead and refrigerate.
I prepare this on Christmas Eve and bake it Christmas morning.
This is one of my family favorites.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and serve with fresh cut vegetables or crackers.

title: jane's pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together except the pecans.
Add chopped pecans and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Decorate top of pie with pecan halves.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350° in center of oven.

title: jingle bell punch
directions: Place spices and tea in saucepan.
Cover with boiling water; cover and steep 3 minutes.
Add sugar.
Cool.
Add remaining liquids and chill.
Serves 18 to 24.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead until smooth. Store in covered container.

title: sausage roll
directions: Brown the sausage and onion, then drain the excess grease. Add the barbecue sauce and grated cheese.

title: soy chicken skillet
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In large skillet, heat oil; brown chicken.
Drain pineapple slices, reserving juice.
Combine 1/2 cup juice, soy sauce, catsup and honey; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with raisins.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken and add pineapple slices.
Cover and simmer another 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Spoon sauce over chicken and pineapple when serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onion and pepper.
Put in bowl.
Add 1/3 cup of sugar and let set.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Slice zucchini thin and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add sliced onion, green pepper, tomatoes, drained olives and chopped parsley.
Pour the salad dressing over the vegetables. Toss and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Smoosh with spatula and remove to a wire rack.
Taste like brownies.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Mix pineapple, flour and sugar. Cook until thick.
Let cool. Slice bananas into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour the pineapple mixture over the nuts.
Mix the coconut with the Cool Whip and spread on top of pie.
Refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving.

title: candied pecans
directions: Simmer all ingredients, but pecans, in a skillet for about 4 minutes, until mixture forms a thread from spoon.
Remove from fire and stir in pecans.
Continue to stir until syrup forms a sugar coating all over the nuts.
Cool separately so the nuts won't stick together.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
In a bowl, mix milk, pancake mix, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Gently fold in oysters (batter will be thick).
Heat oil in a 10-inch frying pan.
Drop batter into hot oil by tablespoons, making sure to include 2 oysters in each portion.
Cook until brown on 1 side (1 to 2 minutes).
Turn carefully and brown the other side.
This makes about 18 fritters. (If batter becomes too thick while standing, thin with oyster liquid.)

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Put dressing in bottom of a greased pan.
Mix water with soup and pour onto dressing.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and put cheese on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: mexicali crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers in bowl.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon on each cracker.
Microwave on High for 25 seconds or longer, if needed.

title: cheddar spinach pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk and seasonings; mix well.
Toss cheese with flour.
Add to eggs.
Stir in spinach.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
Mixture will be thick.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Kids love this.

title: baked apples with meringue
directions: Wash and core apples and place in baking pan.
Fill each apple with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of each. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, syrup and salt to a boil and cook to 240°.
If you don't have a candy thermometer, boil a minute or two.
Add soda and vanilla and stir well.
Pour over corn.
Stir well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour in roaster pan greased well with butter, uncovered.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Lay out on cooling board.
When cool, break up in small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: banana-nut bread i
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch pan. Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Beat together oil, butter and sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one (1) at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in bananas. Gradually beat in flour mixture until well blended. Combine zest and nuts. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon flour over zest and nuts. Toss to coat. Stir into batter. Spoon the batter into prepared pan. Bake until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 minutes. Set pan on a wire rack to cool for 10 minutes. Turn bread out onto rack to cool completely.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Combine corn meal, soda, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix egg and water.
Mix all liquids, then pour into bowl with dry ingredients and stir.
Add 5 tablespoons melted margarine.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade salsa for canning
directions: Chop all ingredients (except tomatoes) in food processor. Pour into large stockpot.
Cook to desired thickness.
Pack into quart jars and can.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add beaten eggs. Sift and add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit bread
directions: Crush fruit with juice in blender.
I prefer canned apricots. Dissolve soda in fruit and add quickly to dry ingredients.
Blend in oil, raisins, nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 4 midget loaves.

title: watergate salad
directions: Sprinkle pudding mix on pineapple.
If there isn't much juice, add 2 tablespoons water.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Instead of adding water, add cranberry juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet 'n hot beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onions and cayenne.
Cook until half done. Stir in sugar and beans.
Simmer a few minutes before serving. This serves two generously.

title: tuna fish roll-ups
directions: Drain tuna fish and mix tuna and egg.
Roll out biscuits.
Put spoonful of tuna mixture on each biscuit.
Fold and pinch with fork.
Makes 10 Tuna Fish Roll-Ups.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve topped with soup.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack first 4 ingredients in jars cold.
Combine next 3 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over okra. Process 5 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet or wok, heat oil; add raw vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
In small bowl combine water, teriyaki sauce, sherry, broth mix and cornstarch. Add to vegetables and stir to combine thoroughly.
Bring to boil. Add chicken and mushrooms.
Reduce heat and let simmer until thoroughly heated.
Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry layer cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, jello, oil, eggs and water.
Add crushed strawberries.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour rectangular baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars, about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.
Each cookie contains 90 calories.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cheese and flavoring. Add color. Mix in xxx sugar. Roll into small balls. Roll in sugar. Press into mint mold and remove onto waxed paper.

title: cassoulet(a french casserole)
directions: In an 8-quart kettle with cover, combine beans with 4 1/2 cups cold water.
Let soak 2 hours, no longer.
Do not drain beans. Meanwhile, pare carrots; cut into quarters.
Peel onions; stud 1 of the onions with whole cloves.
To beans, add chicken broth, bay leaves, 1/2 of the carrots, the onions, celery leaves, 1 teaspoon salt, the black pepper, garlic, thyme, marjoram and sage.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add remaining carrots; cook, covered, 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Brown chicken in vegetable oil.
Add tomato sauce and water. Cook until slightly thickened.
Season with salt to taste.
Put into corn tortillas or shells.
Top with tomato, lettuce and cheese.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box. Bake at 325° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool completely before icing.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw chopped broccoli slightly and break into small pieces.
In medium-sized bowl, combine broccoli, soup, egg, onion, sauce, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix well and pour into square or medium oblong casserole dish.
Crumble enough Ritz crackers to cover mixture (approximately 25 to 30) and dot with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook ground meat.
Add celery, onion and bell pepper.
Add mushroom soup and while mixture is hot, add Cheez Whiz and mix thoroughly.
Add the cooked broccoli and cooked rice.
Mix and place in greased baking dish.
Place in oven and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 18 muffin cups with paper baking cups.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Pour into bottle and refrigerate.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash peppers and remove seeds.
Cut in half and place in large baking dish.
Set aside.

title: holiday punch
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and run on liquefy until smooth.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with graham cracker crust:
1/2 c. butter, 26 graham crackers, 1/4 c. sugar.
Whip 1 pint heavy cream, stiff. Add 1/2 c. sugar.
Fold in gelatin mixture and jello which has been cut in small cubes.
Pour in crust and chill several hours or over night.
A pretty holiday dessert that can be made before.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a jelly roll pan.
I use large cake pan.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl. Whisk oil and eggs in another large bowl until blended and smooth. Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until blended. Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Will be very stiff.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl. Add strawberries and lime juice. Process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Fold in whipped topping. Serve immediately. Yields 5 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain hamburger by putting it in a strainer and rinse under water.
Season with chili powder and pepper.
Toss all ingredients together with salad dressing.
Yield:
16 servings.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 15 g, fat 27 g, calories 379.
One serving (about 1 cup) = 1 bread starch exchange, 2 meat medium fat exchange, 3 fat exchange.

title: carrot bread
directions: Cream together the sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Mix nuts and grated carrots and add to mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peppered roast beef
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Cut inch deep incisions all over roast; insert garlic in slits so they disappear into meat.
Sprinkle meat all over with pepper and place fat side up in roasting pan.
Allow 7 minutes per pound for medium rare.
Do not open door!
Finished roast will be brown, crisp on outside and pink throughout.
Add water to drippings and heat again to pour over thin slices.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Mix the ingredients with the following dressing:

title: cranberry salad
directions: In a food processor, chop the cranberries, walnuts and apple together and set aside.
Dissolve the orange jello and sugar with boiling water.
When this is combined thoroughly, mix in the orange juice; add cranberry mixture. Chill.

title: original chex party mix(finger food)
directions: In small microwave-safe bowl, melt margarine on High.
Add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into 2-gallon, resealable, plastic bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture.
Seal top of bag and shake until all pieces are evenly coated.

title: wilma's harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid. Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar and beat juice or water. Stir over low heat until thickened. Add beets and butter, then heat. Serves 5 to 6.

title: streusel cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding mix in mixing bowl.
Combine oil and vanilla; stir into cake mix.
Add sour cream; blend thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, blending well after each egg with electric mixer on medium speed.
Turn mixer to high speed and beat batter 5 minutes.
Heat Bundt pan in 200° oven for 2 minutes. Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
Turn oven off.
Combine cinnamon, sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Pour some of the cake batter into Bundt pan.
Sprinkle on some of nut mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with cake mixture.
Put cake on oven. Turn oven on to 350°. Bake cake for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: cranberry juice punch
directions: Heat cranberry juice, enough to dissolve sugar.
Chill all ingredients, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: garlic chicken(taste - strong)
directions: Thaw chicken completely.
Discard organ pack.
Wash.
With chicken breast up, starting from back end, work fingers between skin and meat, separating enough for stuffing.
Break up and peel 1 bulb garlic; put through garlic press and mince finely.
Prepare stuffing per directions, using chicken broth for water needed and add 1/2 minced garlic (season to taste).
Take other 1/2 of minced garlic and rub down chicken, inside and out, even under skin. Stuff chicken full with stuffing.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken on rack in baking dish; pour 1/2 to 3/4 cup chicken broth in bottom and 5 to 6 cloves garlic, chopped.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours until done.

title: lemon chicken-grilled
directions: Mix all together, except Worcestershire sauce and salt. Cook slow, then add Worcestershire sauce and salt. After chicken is tender, brush on while still cooking on the grill.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add flour. Add milk, starting and ending with flour. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Mix well. Grease and flour tube pan. Pour in mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Makes a very delicious crusty cake. Take out of pan as soon as done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, butter and grated cheese, then add milk, eggs and onion.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes in a casserole dish.

title: dutch apple roll
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in the shortening; add milk.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread chopped apples over the dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as a jelly roll; cut in slices and arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
(Roll of dough may be wrapped in foil and frozen to be sliced and baked later.)

title: tacos
directions: Heat taco shells according to package directions.
Meanwhile, for filling, in a large skillet, cook meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in chilie peppers and chili powder; heat through.
Fill taco shell with meat mixture; top with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Layer salad on individual plates and pour dressing over or combine all ingredients with dressing in large salad bowl.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted margarine and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes in 400° oven.
Set aside to cool.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda. Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter in a separate bowl. Add egg and vanilla to shortening-sugar mixture. Work in dry ingredients. Shape into teaspoon sized balls and place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Top each cookie with a candy Kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edges. Return to oven and bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: salgadinhos de queijo
directions: Mix all the ingredients, working the dough until it does not stick to your hands.
Roll out the dough on a lightly floured surface until it is thin like pie crust.
Cut into pieces, about 1 x 3-inches.
Make 2 or 3 cuts into one of the short ends and spread the pieces apart like a fan.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown, stirring a few at a time.
(They cook quickly.)
As soon as they come out of the oil, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together all but almonds; put in casserole and top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 14 minutes.
Serve at party with crackers or rye bread (small slices).

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Mix well and add small amount of water, if needed.
Sprinkle remaining chips over bottom of pan.
Pour mix into pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Check for doneness.
If needed, cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in oil.
Remove meat and lower heat. Add garlic and next 8 seasonings.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Do not burn.
Return meat.
Mix tomato paste with water and pour over meat.
Bring to full boil.
Lower heat and cover loosely.
Simmer slowly about 2 to 3 hours, turning meat occasionally.
When meat is tender, cook noodles and drain.
Slice roast and arrange with noodles and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and chives.

title: tousey creek fried potatoes
directions: Layer the potatoes, onions, bacon, and mushrooms on Reynolds wrap.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Tuck the corners of Reynolds wrap to not leak and lay on grill.
Flip on grill until done.
Can also be cooked in oven.

title: ladyfingers(cookies)
directions: Mix all together and roll in small shapes.
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Then roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour ice cube/orange juice mixture into blender; add remaining ingredients and blend.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until mixture spins a thread.
Add peanuts; cook until peanuts are done, then 1 minute longer.
Add the butter, baking soda and salt; stir well.
Pour into a greased baking sheet to cool.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat in graham cracker crust in a pan.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese and sugar until soft.
Pour on top of the mixture. Slice banana on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread cherry pie filling on top.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: squash chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients except morsels. Mix well with spoon and add Toll House morsels.
Mix.
Pour or spoon into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Let cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown turkey or beef and drain. Add enchilada sauce, soup, chilies and mix. Layer tortilla chips, meat mixture and cheese in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Bake at 350° until bubbly. (This is a good low fat dish.)

title: barbecue quail
directions: Split quail down back and brown in deep fat.
Pour off all fat and pour the following sauce over them.
Cook slowly for about 2 hours, basting frequently with the sauce.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in fat.
Add enough water to make a soft dough, but not sticky.
Knead well.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Great in individual bags, tied.
Send to school instead of candy for Halloween or any occasion.

title: cheddar scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Reduce to low heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
May add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and melt.

title: pie supreme
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until it does not shake in middle of pie, about 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake in bag the first 4 ingredients.
Melt
on stove the brown sugar, butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and shake in bag.
Pile into a greased Bundt pan with hole in center.
Pour brown sugar, butter and cinnamon mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Great fun for kids!

title: hot sauce
directions: Blend in blender for a smooth texture.
Stir together for a chunky sauce.
Serve hot or cold.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients together.
Cream butter or shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed until light and fluffy.
On low speed, beat in flour mixture alternately with 1/2 cup sweet milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat only until smooth.
Dust 1 1/4 cups fresh blueberries lightly with flour.
Fold berries gently into batter.
Fill greased muffin cups with batter 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve warm.

title: romanian stuffed cantaloupe(pepene galben umplut)
directions: Peel and seed and cube the apples peaches, plums and pears, slice grapes in half.
Place all fruit in a large bowl and mix with 1 Tbsp. of sugar.
Cut a slice off the top of the cantaloupe large enough to remove seeds with a spoon.
After seeded place all fruits inside the cantaloupe, press fruit in gently so it fits.
In a small saucepan heat wine and remaining sugar to a bowl, add gelatine and mix well until it dissolves well, add vanilla.
When mixture cools pour into cantaloupe to cover fruits, place in refrigerator for 2-4 hours or until well chilled.
Cut cantaloupe in half and then into slices.
Serve.

title: shrimp etouffee(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Brown flour and oil until dark brown (cocoa colored).
Add onions.
Stir until clear.
Add balance of ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring to boiling; reduce to simmer.
Cover; cook one hour.
Add shrimp.
Cook for 20 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: texas pecan country chicken
directions: On
hard
surface with meat mallet, pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Sprinkle
with
salt and pepper.
Saute mushrooms
and onion
in
butter.
Cool.
Mix
with
cream cheese, mustard
and thyme.
Divide into 4 equal portions and spread on each piece of chicken.
Fold
over
ends
and roll up, pressing edges to seal. Mix pecans,
bread
crumbs and parsley in bowl. Dip chicken into butter,
then
into
crumbs,
turning to coat. Place on greased baking sheet seam side down.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt
the unsweetened chocolate.
Add vanilla and nuts. Mix other
ingredients	with
the
chocolate mixture.
Bake in shallow greased pan
at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until light brown.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Mix well.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter or margarine.
Pour into pastry shell.
Swirl meringue on filling. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: In electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and milk.
Set heat control to 280°.
Bring mixture to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into 8-inch buttered pan. Chill and then cut into squares.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Preparation: 30 minutes (20 minutes for rice to cook). Cooking Time: 30 minutes.
Temperature: 350°.

title: doritos casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
In saucepan, bring soup, water and tomatoes to a boil.
Put a layer of Doritos (slightly crushed) into bottom of casserole dish, then top with a layer of ground beef, then soup, then Doritos until all ingredients are used.
Top with cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: eggs regina
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Mix well.
Cut eggs in halves.
Press eggs slowly into mixture.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add onion, carrots, potatoes and bean sprouts.
Stir together well.
Add soy sauce and garlic powder (to taste).
Mix well.
Cover and let simmer for about 10 minutes. Stir well again, taste and then let simmer again for 10 minutes. Set mixture aside and let cool.
When cool, follow directions on egg roll wrapper and roll.
This makes 8 to 10 dozen egg rolls. These can be frozen and taken out as needed.
After rolled, cook in preheated skillet of oil until just brown.

title: spanish cream dessert salad(mary huber)
directions: Combine gelatin, 1/4 cup sugar and salt.
Stir 1/2 cup cold milk, let stand one minute.
Beat egg yolks and milk.
Stir milk mixture into gelatin mixture.
Stir constantly over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Don't boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill 30 to 45 minutes (until it mounds).
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in rest of sugar (slowly).
Fold in gelatin.
Chill 5 hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vinegar, vegetable oil, salt, sugar, water and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let cool.
Drain French beans, bean sprouts, peas and corn.
Mix with celery, pepper, onions and carrots.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: breakfast hash
directions: In small microwave bowl, combine all ingredients, stirring completely, until foamy.
Cook on High for 1 minute in microwave; remove and stir again.
Cook for approximately 1 more minute or until done to your likeness.
Serve with toast and orange juice and enjoy!!

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel.
Beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
May frost with confectioners sugar drizzle frosting, but they are good just plain.

title: walnut crescents cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape dough like 1/4 moons. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
When cookies are ready, take out of oven.
Roll each cookie in confectioners sugar or in a dish.

title: oatmeal butterscotch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and all sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats and chips; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy or 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix margarine, 1 egg and cake mix. Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan from center out. Mix 3 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes. Will rise while baking and fall when cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles normally, then mix tuna fish, soup, noodles, peas, water and milk.
Mix well with noodles.
Put in oven for 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Top will look crusty.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour over baked crust and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar while hot.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: refrigerated bread and butter pickles
directions: The syrup is a cold pack. Mix sugar, vinegar and spices together. Sterilize jars of various sizes with lids. Pack into sterile jars the slices of cucumbers with onion slices. Pack tight. Pour cold syrup over cucumbers. Seal jars. Refrigerate. No hot water bath! Every day for 1 week, turn jars upside down, blending ingredients. Cucumbers will shrivel up in this process. Ready to eat after 1 week. Will keep 6 months in refrigerator. This recipe can be made all year round. Good for gift giving. Serves many.
Pickles are crisp and delicious. Great for picnics!

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix with 1 cup milk as directed on package. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup cookies and the "rocks" into pudding mixture.

title: cherokee huckleberry bread
directions: Cream eggs, butter and sugar together.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Sprinkle flour on berries to prevent them from going to the bottom.
Add berries to mixture.
Put in baking pan and bake in oven at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until done.

title: mexican chicken(club member: brigitte magee)
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Heat soup and Ro-Tel in a boiler.
In a casserole dish, layer crushed Doritos, chicken, soup and grated cheese. Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: easy cinnamon puffs
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Divide dough into 12 equal pieces.
Form into balls.
Dip each ball in melted butter.
Roll, one at a time, in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Place each ball in greased cup of muffin pan.
Let rise until doubled. Bake at 375°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove while warm.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown beef on all sides. Remove beef and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic, stirring until onion is translucent.

Mix in beef and add paprika, tomatoes, tomato sauce, pepper and sugar. Cover and simmer over lowest heat 1 hour. Remove cover and simmer 15 minutes longer. Stir in sour cream and serve over noodles. Garnish with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: Get cream cheese at room temperature.
Add all ingredients except pie crust into blender.
Blend until mixed well.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Can eat plain or top with favorite fruit (cherries, strawberries or blueberries).

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put roast in pan with water. Cover with foil. Bake at 250° overnight. (I put roast in around 10:00 p.m. and take it out around 7:00 a.m.)

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat spinach with water until thawed.
Add butter.
Heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Do not drain.
Stir in bread cubes and seasonings.
Turn into casserole.
Toss crumbs, Parmesan cheese and butter.
Spread over spinach.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until hot through.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and cool. Place in large bowl and add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together and put in foil-lined container.
Let set at least 48 hours.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Melt a few chocolate chips and swirl in.
Pour into pie crust. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned pull taffy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and cream of tartar.
Place over heat.
Stir until sugar dissolves; cook without stirring to 265° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add coloring and flavoring if desired.
Pour on greased platter or pie pan.
Cool until easily handled.
Pull into ropes until chalky and porous. Break or cut into bite size pieces.

title: bread filling
directions: Saute celery and onions in melted oleo until lightly browned. Place cubed bread in large bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix until moistened.
Stuff into turkey.
Bake remainder in greased casserole at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together the soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Heat until warmed up.
Add to green beans; mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put onion rings over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ranch snack mix
directions: In two large bowls combine the pretzels, bugles, cashews and crackers.
Sprinkle with dressing mix using 1/2 in each bowl. Toss gently to combine.
Drizzle with oil, toss until well coated. Store in airtight containers.
Makes a great party snack.
tags: bite size cheddar cheese fish crackers

title: irish soda bread
directions: Soak raisins in warm water for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Heavily grease and bake in iron skillet.
Be sure to prick with a fork before baking and cut cross on top 1-inch deep.
Brush baked bread with butter and margarine to prevent crumbling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring often.
Stir a little of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks and add to saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, butter and peanut butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: rice and corn bake
directions: Drain corn.
Cut up Velveeta cheese.
Chop onion and bell pepper; saute in skillet with 1 stick of butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spam salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Add peas, celery, olives and onion.
Add mayonnaise.
Add Spam that has been diced.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomato wedges just before serving.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart glass dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sopa paraguaya(paraguayan cornbread)
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Remove from heat and add milk, cornmeal and cheese.
Beat egg yolks and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture carefully.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake in 375° oven until light gold on top.
Cut into squares.
For less cholesterol, delete egg yolks.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream together margarine, peanut butter, orange rind and vanilla.
Add egg, orange juice and artificial sweetener; blend well.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well after each addition.
Add raisins; mix well.
Mix 1 level tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Roll between hands to form ball.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered tin.
Tastes better 24 hours after baking.
Makes 12 servings.
Yield:
24 cookies.
One serving, 2 cookies.

title: holiday stars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, lemon rind and milk.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well; chill 1 hour.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 144 stars or any other holiday pattern you would like.
Cut 1-inch holes in center of half the stars.
Bake on a cookie sheet in preheated 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool; spread with jam or jelly on solid cookies.
Top each with cookie with hole in center.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: larry's chocolate chip cookies(3 dozen)
directions: Blend butter, brown sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.
Add flour, salt and baking soda; mix.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for soft and 11 to 15 minutes for crisp.

title: vegetable salad mold
directions: "All wholesome food is caught without a net or a trap." - William Blake

title: frozen chocolate mousse torte
directions: In a bowl of a food processor or the small bowl of an electric mixer, break almond paste into small pieces.
Add cocoa and two of the eggs.
Whirl or beat until mixture is smooth.
Pour into a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: herb - roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place potatoes on a baking sheet and drizzle with olive oil.
Using hands, toss to coat evenly.
Season potatoes with salt and pepper.
Bake 10 minutes; using spatula, turn potatoes.
Toss with herbs and bake until golden and tender, approximately 15 more minutes.

title: green chilies
directions: Spread chilies in bottom of a buttered glass 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs with water and drizzle over cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Prepare potatoes as package indicates (do not bake).
Combine soup, chicken and vegetables and stir into potatoes.
Place mixture in an uncovered, greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: corn and cheese pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Gradually stir in milk.
Lower heat and cook, stirring constantly until the mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix well and pour into a buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Set casserole in pan of hot water. Bake in the water bath for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Mix together in order.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water; fold in slowly.
Fill papers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: In medium saucepan, combine onion, sugar, garlic powder, catsup, pineapple liquid, lemon juice and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Skin, bone and cut chicken into 3 x 1-inch strips. In a plastic bag, toss chicken with flour to coat.
In a large skillet over medium heat, cook chicken in hot oil 4 to 5 minutes or until lightly browned.
Arrange cooked chicken and pineapple in an ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is hot and sauce is bubbly.
Serve over hot rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Boil shrimp in water until tender.
Cut in half.
In frying pan, melt butter.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Slightly brown.
Mix all other ingredients except croutons and cheese and mix in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add croutons, then cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients in order and mix thoroughly.
Bake in layer cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes on high.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pumpkin.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, ginger and nutmeg.
Pour into wax paper lined jelly roll pan and cover with 1 cup of chopped pecans.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and roll in powdered sugared towel and let cool.
Be sure to roll towel and cake together.
When cooled, unroll and spread with filling.

title: kem - tone salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Dissolve jello in hot water and let thicken. Meanwhile, mix milk with cheese.
Add to jello and then add nuts and pineapple.
Chill until set.
I mostly double the recipe.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix again.
Chill and serve.

title: date fingers
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan and heat on medium until well dissolved and completely melted.
Remove from heat and add next 3 ingredients.
Blend thoroughly; cool and shape into fingers, then roll fingers in 4x confectioners sugar to coat well. Spread out on flat surface in cool place to set and become firm. Yield:
5 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole. Place bread over bottom. Cover with layer of sausage, then a layer of cheese. Beat together well the eggs, milk and salt, then pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Next day, uncover casserole and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon sticks
directions: Wrap bacon around bread sticks (barber's pole fashion).
Place on paper plate and paper towel to absorb fat.
Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Place sticks in a mug to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight and then boil until tender, about 1 hour. Add salt, oil, tomato soup, brown sugar and onion.
Mix and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese; pour into pie crust.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and then put frosting on cake.

title: easy stewfort collins, colorado
directions: Place beef (no need to brown) in 3 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, basil and pepper.
Top with celery, carrot and onions. Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat and vegetables, coating all pieces.
Cover tightly and bake in slow oven (300°) for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: chicken dorito
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Mix soups, cheese and Ro-Tel; heat on low until cheese is melted.
Layer 1/2 bag of crushed chips in a 9 x 12-inch pan, then layer chicken.
Cover with cheese, soup and Ro-Tel mixture.
Top with remaining chips.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: quick stroganoff
directions: Brown stew meat in skillet.
Mix soup and milk until creamy. Mix into stew meat and drippings.
Boil noodles according to directions, rinse and drain.
Pour meat and soup mixture over noodles.
Serve hot with biscuits or cornbread.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Put chicken, cut up and boned, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken broth with soup and pour over chicken.
Mix flour and milk with melted margarine; pour over chicken.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: easy party meatballs
directions: *Or 2 pounds wieners or smoky link sausage.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Slice bread about 1-inch thick and lay on cookie sheet.
Mix Lawry's garlic spread with margarine as directed on jar.
Spread mixture on 1 side of bread only.
Spread on top to cover each slice.
Place in broiler until golden brown.

title: quickie casserole with hamburger
directions: Put potatoes in buttered casserole.
Put the meat on top of the potatoes.
Mix soups and onion and spread over meat.
Top with chips.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eggless milkless chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and pour in 2 cups water.
Mix with spoon, then beat with mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and soda.
Add oil; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots and mix well. Bake at 350°.
Makes three layers.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, jalapeno peppers, salt, pepper and cumin; drain well.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Add grated Cheddar until the dip is correct consistency.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: yummy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare chocolate cake batter according to directions on package.
Bake 2/3 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan and let cool.

title: shrimp lo mein
directions: In small bowl, whisk together 1 cup water, the broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, oyster sauce and ginger for sauce. Cook fettuccine following package directions. Drain in large bowl toss with sesame oil. Heat wok or large skillet over high heat. Add 1 tablespoon vegetable oil. Add shrimp; stir-fry until ping and cooked, 3 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon to plate. Add remaining oil. Add scallions, garlic, snap peas and red peppers to wok; stir-fry for 5 minutes. Add sauce; simmer and cook 30 seconds. Stir in sprouts, then fettuccine and shrimp; mix to thoroughly coat and heat through, about 1 minute.

title: corn biscuits
directions: Bake in 10 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place butter in pan and melt.
Mix Bisquick and corn.
Drop by spoonfuls and turn when placing in dish.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Bake in cake pan (approximate size 9 x 13-inch) for about 30 to 40 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: mustard sauce supreme
directions: Mix sugar and mustard together and sift.
Place in saucepan and add remaining ingredients.
Cook very slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles, then continue cooking for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Makes 1 quart.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Cook beef in oil (brown).
Add other ingredients, except soup water and cabbage.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add soup and water and mix.
Remove from heat.
Place cabbage in 2-quart casserole.
Pour meat mixture over cabbage.
Do not mix.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: pound cake with wine
directions: Use electric mixer to combine eggs, oil, wine, cake mix, pudding and nutmeg.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. While cake is still warm, dust with powdered sugar.

title: rice
directions: First oil the onions.
When the onions get red, the onions should get red in between 1 to 10 minutes.
Then put Spice Blends, also red and green peppers.
Also tomato can be added.
Last, water and rice can be added.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, stir Pet milk, marshmallows and frozen orange juice concentrate until marshmallows melt.
Take off heat.
Stir in dates, raisins, walnuts, candied fruit and candied cherries.
Stir until well blended.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 2 eggs and 1 stick of butter/oleo (melted) together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, mix the powdered sugar, 2 eggs, cheese and 1 stick of butter/oleo (melted) together.
Pour over other mixture.
Do not mix the two together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef chop suey
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add celery and onion.
Cook slowly until tender.
Add ground beef.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and bean sprouts; mix well and heat.
Serve with thin soy sauce as a condiment.
Serves 4.

title: lentil patty
directions: Combine lentils, salt, water and rice; bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Cover, then simmer until tender, about 35 minutes.
Remove; let stand 10 minutes.
Wash with water.
Stir in bread crumbs, wheat germ, onion, celery seed, etc.
Shape into patties; roll in the wheat germ.
Fry slowly in well-oiled pan for 10 minutes. These are delicious.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat milk and pudding mix; chill.
Mix soft cream cheese and butter; add powdered sugar.
Stir chilled pudding mix into cream cheese mixture.
Add Cool Whip to mixture.

title: chicken pilau
directions: Boil chicken about 1 hour.
When done, take out liquid and debone.
Reserve liquid to cook 2 cups rice.
Add celery, onion, soy sauce, Tabasco, Lipton onion soup mix, salt and pepper and cut up chicken.
Cook until rice is done.

title: vegetable frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan (or spray pan with Pam).
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and saute until tender-crisp, about 15 to 20 minutes.
While vegetables are cooking, whisk the eggs and milk together in a large mixing bowl. Stir in bread and cheeses.
Season with pepper.
Add drained sauteed vegetables to egg mixture and stir until well combined. Pour into pan and pack mixture tightly.
Place pan on a baking sheet to catch any leaks.
Bake until Frittata is firm to the touch, puffed and golden brown, about 1 hour.
If top is getting too brown, cover with aluminum foil.
Serve hot, at room temperature, or cold.
It can be reheated in a 350° oven until warmed through or in microwave.
Freezes well.

title: quick breakfast treats
directions: Separate refrigerated
biscuits.
Mix
small amounts of cinnamon and sugar until it looks right.
Roll each biscuit in melted butter until
covered
on
top, bottom and sides.
Then roll them in
the
cinnamon-sugar mixture, coating the bottom, top and sides.

title: southern cobbler
directions: Place fruit in 9-inch square dish.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; mix well and sprinkle over fruit.
Dot with oleo.
Place pastry on top of fruit; trim edge and seal.
Make several slits to allow steam to escape.
Brush pastry with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Chill. Serve with any seafood; especially good with fried shrimp.

title: strawberry marmalade
directions: Peel outer layer of oranges and lemons; set aside.
Remove the white membrane from fruit and discard.
Set the fruit aside.
Chop peels; place in a large saucepan.
Add water and baking soda. Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Cut in little pieces.
Heat flour, egg, vinegar, sugar and water (a little at a time) to make like a gravy.
Add bacon pieces.
Heat until thick, always stirring. Pour over lettuce or endive.

title: reuben casserole(a popular sandwich idea, translated into a casserole)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with layer of corned beef and then cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and salad dressing and spread over cheese.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Stir bread crumbs into melted margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Top with dash of caraway seed.
Bake for 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: aunt katies brown bread
directions: Mix the sugar, raisins, soda, salt, butter and boiling water. Let this mixture stand overnight.
The next day, add the egg and the flour and blend well.
Bake for 1 hour plus at 350° or 325° for
glass pan.
Check after 1 hour.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa 1 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture comes to a boil.
Remove and add oats, coconut and vanilla.
Beat well; spoon onto waxed paper.
Tastes like fudge.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green peppers in skillet.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and pork and beans to ground beef, mix well. Cook in slow oven or crock-pot for 2 hours or bake for 30 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 9 to 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Don't look at the cake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip scones
directions: Whisk together flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in butter. Add whipping cream and egg. Add chocolate chips. Cut out into circles. Bake at 375° until golden on top.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk, marshmallow cream, butter and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts. Spread in a 8-inch square pan.
Makes around 30 pieces.

title: bed and breakfast cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put about 1 heaping teaspoonful about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Put syrup into tall glass.
Add sparkling water and stir.
Add ice cream and stir.
Add more sparkling water to fill glass.

title: nassau royale chocolate mousse
directions: Mix Nassau Royale, rum and 1/4 c. sugar, heat to dissolve. Melt 1 pkg chocolate chips (6 oz), stir in the rum mix, let cool. Whip 2 egg whites to death in the blender, adding Balsamic vinegar and/or cream of tartar to help stiffen.
Add to cool chocolate/rum mix.
Stir in Cool Whip, fill wine glasses and chill.

title: almond pine cones
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often until almonds just begin to turn color.
Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise, bacon, dill and pepper; mix well.
Cover; chill overnight.
Form cheese mixture into shapes of 2 pine cones on a serving platter.
Begin at narrow end and press almonds at a slight angle into cheese mixture in rows.
Continue overlapping rows until cheese is covered.
Garnish with artificial pine sprigs.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Do not freeze.

title: italian bread
directions: Proof the yeast with the water, then add sugar and oil or margarine.
Add salt to flour and gradually add flour.
Knead dough and shape it into 2 loaves; let it rise until its size is doubled.
Brush with egg white before baking for 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until brown; drain.
Stir in the salt, oregano, pepper, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and green pepper.
Prepare pie crust.
Pour meat mixture into pie plate.
Spread cheese topping over meat.

title: little layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 2 to 3 heaping serving spoonfuls in each greased 9-inch cake pan lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until done, not brown.
Will make 12 to 15 layers.

title: cream chicken tacos
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add green chilies, broth, sauce, half and half, cheese and chicken.
Line casserole with uncooked tortillas. Alternate sauce and tortillas in layers.
Let stand at least 2 hours before baking to improve flavors.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
Freezes very well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken supreme overnight
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into greased casserole.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Let stand 1 hour out of refrigerator before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Mix and pour into ring mold.

title: the best lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until beef is well browned, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano, thyme, pepper, garlic salt and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf; spoon off any fat.
Prepare lasagna noodles as directed on box.
Arrange noodles in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Place 1/2 mixture over first layer of noodles, then 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Cover lettuce, onion,
celery,	peas,
water chestnuts, mayonnaise and sugar with Cheddar cheese, bacon bits, eggs and tomatoes.
Layer as listed	except	last
one.
This should be made
several hours
before
serving
or
night
before.
Just before serving, add
1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Don't toss. If desired, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: banana cream brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions; stir in peanuts.
Bake in a well greased 9 by 9-inch baking dish according to package directions.
Set aside to cool.
Place bananas in a single layer over brownies.
Whisk pudding into milk, then add cool whip and pour over bananas.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: broccoli dip
directions: In very large pot, heat broccoli (careful not to overcook); drain well.
Put back in large pot or very large mixing pan. Saute onion in butter until just done, but not burned.
Add onion mixture to broccoli.
Then add to mixture all other ingredients.

title: apple krisp
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with sliced apples.
Mix all dry ingredients and egg until crumbly.
Spread over top of apples. Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pin money pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in fresh water for 2 days or until fresh enough. Soak other things in water with handful of salt overnight. Cook in vinegar, sugar and spices for 1 hour, slowly.

title: baked onion
directions: In Pyrex dish, place four large onions.
Quarter each onion and place a pat of butter in each quarter.
Place a heaping tablespoon of dark brown sugar on top of each onion.
Cut a piece of bacon in half and crisscross on top of onion.
Cover and bake in a preheated 325° oven for an hour or until onions are tender.
Salt and pepper a little.
Serves 4.

title: egg, cheese and olive casserole
directions: Butter an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Alternate layers of bread, cheese and olives. Beat eggs and combine dry mustard and milk. Pour over bread and cheese layers. Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with green olives and serve.

title: endive salad
directions: Wash and chop the endive.
Fry bacon until crisp; remove from drippings; crumble.
Mix salt, sugar and flour; add vinegar.
Stir until well blended.
Cook sauce in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings until thickened, adding cream gradually.
Pour mixture over endive and mix together lightly.
Garnish with chopped eggs and crumbled bacon.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, strawberry gelatin, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan. Stir in boiling water.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Arrange whole strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries. Chill several hours.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix together the margarine, sugar and cocoa. Add the eggs, one at a time, flour, baking powder, nuts and coconut. Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. While cake is still hot, spread the marshmallow cream on top and let cool.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl and mix together.
Don't put apples higher than 1 1/2 inches.
Butter glass Pyrex, 12 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pan.
