Lay apples evenly, covering the whole pan.

title: superb london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients, except steak, to make marinade.
Place steak in marinade for 24 hours.
Grill until desired doneness.

title: neiman marcus brownies
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 stick of melted butter, 1 egg and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Press into 9X13 pan.
Cream together the remaining 1 stick melted butter, cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Spread over the cake mixture.
Sprinkle with pecans and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Top should be firm and lightly browned.

title: apple streusel cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spread apple filling in buttered 9-inch square baking pan. In medium bowl, beat eggs. Add condensed milk, melted butter, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Pour over apple filling.
In medium bowl, combine sugar and flour. Cut in cold butter until crumbly. Add nuts and oats. Sprinkle over custard. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: 3 cheese spread
directions: *Or use 5 pepper blend.

title: chicken 'n cheese
directions: Place seasoned chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with soup diluted with wine or 1/2 cup of water.
Cover generously with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs. Drizzle melted butter over the top.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread pineapple and syrup.
Spread pie filling over pineapple; put dry cake mix over pie filling; sprinkle pecans over cake mix; press into cake mix.
Slice margarine and place evenly over pecans.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Beat the eggs and place in a saucepan with the sugar, flour and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside. Mix together the apples, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour on the dressing mixture and combine well.
Fold in the Kool Whip and store in the refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
Makes 10-12 servings.

title: brownie pie(microwave)
directions: Mix well. Pour into glass pie plate. Bake in microwave 5 to 7 minutes on Medium or 50% power, turning plate twice, then 1 to 3 minutes on High power.

title: quick energy gorp
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 cups.

title: warm scallop-rice salad(makes 1 serving)
directions: In 1-quart microwavable casserole, combine leek, pepper and garlic.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 minutes, until leek is tender.
Add rice and 3/4 cup water and stir to combine. Microwave uncovered on High for 5 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.
Cover and microwave on Medium for 3 minutes. Add scallops.
Cover and microwave on Medium for 3 minutes.
Let stand for 1 minute until scallops are opaque.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Serve over greens, if desired.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 3 1/2 tablespoons of mixture to make a cup of cappuccino.

title: spicy artichoke dip with jalapenos
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: garden pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or golden brown.
Cool.

title: spice muffins
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and pumpkin pie spice; set aside.
In large bowl, combine cereal, sugar and milk. Let stand 3 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg whites and oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined. Portion batter evenly into 12 lightly greased muffins pan cups. Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dressing
directions: Combine all
ingredients except broth, butter and eggs. Toss well.
Add
broth, butter and eggs.
Mix well, but lightly. Should be
very
moist.
Use
to stuff neck and body cavities of turkey.
Or for ease in preparation and serving, cook separately in a well-greased baking dish, 45 minutes at 325°. Makes about 11 to 12 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart glass container, microwave sugar and syrup on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes.
Add soda and stir until foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces.

title: fruit salad
directions: (Use any fruit you like.)

title: ron's monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; 1/4 cup for each cookie on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fried shrimp taffine
directions: Crush ginger root and garlic together.
Set aside.
Mix next five ingredients and set aside.
Heat oil in uncovered wok at 375°.
Add ginger root and garlic.
Stir-fry 10 seconds.
Add shrimp.
Stir-fry 3 minutes or until pink.
Add green onions. Stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add soy sauce mixture. Stir-fry 30 seconds. Brown bean sprouts, zucchini and sesame seed in butter.
Add to stir-fry mixture.
Serve immediately.
For hotter tate, use 1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper.

title: pear relish
directions: Peel and grind in food chopper until you have 1 gallon of pears.
Place in a large pan and add 1 cup salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out all juice and then add ingredients.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: spicy roast turkey
directions: Remove mesh from turkey and flatten turkey on a cutting board, skin side down.
Combine garlic, rosemary, pepper and salt in a blender.
Turn on motor and gradually add oil until this is chopped coarsely.
Spread half the garlic mixutre over inside of turkey.
Reroll turkey to its original log shape, tying firmly every two inches.
Spread remaining mixture on the outside.
Roast on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 170°.
Remove from oven and let stand 20 minutes.
Remove strings and slice.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and butter. Cook, stirring over medium heat, until thick, about 15 minutes. Add coconut, pecans, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Stir until desired consistency.
Cool. Makes enough for one 13 x 9 cake.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water to strawberry Jell-O mix.
Add frozen strawberries and mix until the strawberries are thawed.
Add
can of pineapple and juice and the mashed bananas.
Pour half the mixture in dish; set in refrigerator until firm.
Take out and spread the sour cream.
Add remaining 1/2 that has been setting out.
Refrigerate.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and nuts.
Put in fridge.

title: bran muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk mixture and stir.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18-20 minutes. Muffin batter may be stored in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin, leaving peel on.
Chop onions and peppers; combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours. Drain well.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to boil. Add the liquid you drained off cucumbers.
Heat but do not boil. Seal in jars.

title: pepper steak
directions: Tenderize round steak by pounding. Cut into strips.
Brown meat in hot oil in a large skillet.

Remove to dish. Add more oil and cook garlic, onion and pepper until tender. Return meat to pan. Pour 1 can of soup over meat and cook until done. May need to add more soup during cooking. Sprinkle on soy sauce to taste. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Make crust of flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 cup margarine and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Press crust into a 10 x 15-inch dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: minute caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and cream. Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil (turn heat back to high).
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat immediately.
When mixture begins to lose its gloss, spread quickly over cake in pan, while hot.
Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Saute onion and garlic cloves in oil.
Add zucchini and saute. Put half of the zucchini and onion mixture into casserole dish. Add a layer of sauce, then garlic salt and Italian seasoning.
Add layer of Provolone and remainder of zucchini and more seasonings, then rest of Provolone.
Top with sauce, then Parmesan and seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix together.
Spread on slice of bread.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cut, cook and mix in big pan.
Put in quart jars and can at 10 pounds pressure for 25 minutes.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Chill for several hours.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine everything.
Stir in meat; mix well.
On wax paper, pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of the meat.
Leave a small margin around the edges.
Sprinkle cheese over ham.
Roll like a jelly roll.
Seal edges and ends.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
During the last 5 minutes, place Velveeta cheese slices on top.

title: chocolate yummy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over butter.
Mix peanut butter and condensed milk and spoon over crumbs.
Sprinkle granola chips and coconut over top.
Press down gently.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cheesy grits
directions: Stir grits and salt into briskly boiling water in a large saucepan.
Return to boil, then reduce heat and cook 2 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and cheese.
Stir; let stand a few minutes until desired consistency.
Serve hot.

title: great burgers
directions: Combine onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Add beef and mix well. Shape into 8 patties. Grill burgers. When done top with crumbled bacon and cheese. Continue to grill until cheese melts. Serve on warm buns with miracle whip, lettuce, tomatoes and pickles.

title: braised steak
directions: Flour and brown steaks in shortening.
Remove steaks and brown onions
in
shortening.
Add
remaining ingredients.
Add water to
make as much gravy as you desire (don't start adding too much water at the beginning) as it cooks.
Simmer for three hours. Cool
overnight.
Skim
off fat;
thicken with flour or cornstarch.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix everything and cook on medium.
Stir until the dough forms a ball and comes off the side of the pan.
Cool and knead.
Divide and color.
Store in airtight container.
Add a little baby powder to make it smell like Play Dough.
Have fun!

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into greased muffin tin. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: nancy's tuna casserole
directions: Mix bisquick and water to form crust.
Place in 9 inch x 9 inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and place in shell. Put paprika on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: golden rhubarb jam(50 year old recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Let stand until sugar is almost dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.

title: black-eyed peas and sausage
directions: Crumble sausage and brown with chopped onion in large frying pan. Drain grease. Add black-eyed peas, tomatoes, chili powder and pepper. Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked bacon appetizers
directions: Put bacon strips on broiler pan covered with foil. Cover with brown sugar. Broil at 350° to 400°.
Start on middle shelf, then move to lower shelf until crisp.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Grease cookie sheet and sides.
Line with wax paper.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn upside down on a tea towel, dusted with 4x sugar.
Pull off wax paper.
Roll tightly and cool.
Unroll and fill.
Reroll and refrigerate.

title: pizza pop up
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Add mushrooms, sauce and seasonings. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Cut butter and pecans into dry ingredients.
Crumble over the fruit and bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° preheated oven.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in buttered baking dish.
Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, long and slowly until bread browns a bit, at least 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: magic bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Melt margarine in a 9x13 glass dish. Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle morsels, coconut, and nuts evenly.
Press down lightly.
Bake 25 -30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Allow to cool before cutting into bars.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: 1st Layer: Cream butter and flour.
Add nuts and make a crust in bottom of oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix sugar, eggs and syrup well.
Add salt, vanilla and melted butter and mix well.
Fold in pecans last.
Bake at 450° on bottom rack for 5 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350°.
When pie starts to brown, turn oven down to 350° and cook until center of pie is firm and done.

title: spiced apples
directions: Wash and core apples.
Slice into rings.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with hearts.
Pour boiling water over.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: beef crock-pot
directions: Place all in crock-pot on high 7 hours.
Do not add water. It makes its own juice.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Hull strawberries.
In covered blender container at medium speed, blend whole berries and remaining ingredients until smooth. Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve soup in chilled bowls or cups.
Garnish with sliced strawberries.
Makes 3 servings or 2 2/3 cups.

title: party mix
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients in a large microwave-safe bowl. Mix well. Stir in next 4 ingredients and mix well. Microwave on High for 6 minutes. Stir 1/2 way through cooking. Add nuts and mix well. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. Makes about 7 cups.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put all ingredients in thick saucepan.
Cook on medium heat to 225°.
Add 1 1/2 to 3 cups of peanuts.
Cook to 295°.
Cut heat. Add 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir well. Pour in buttered pie pans.
Cool.
Break in pieces.

title: fruity waffles
directions: Pop waffles in toaster.
Top with fruit and Cool Whip.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Cut up oranges and mix with pineapple, cottage cheese and jello.
Beat until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in saucepan.
Add peppers and bring to a boil.
Turn burner off and let mixture set for 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Fry bacon and sausage; cut in 1-inch pieces.
Drain on paper towels.
Dump most of grease; use same skillet to saute onion, celery, mushrooms and parsley.
Put bread cubes in a large bowl. Sprinkle with sage, thyme and pepper.
Add meat and other ingredients to bread.
Toss with large spoon until bread is wet. If needed, add water.
Dump into greased cake pan.
Bake at 350°, covered, 30 minutes, then bake uncovered 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hot cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grate cheese.
Let cheese and margarine stand at room temperature until soft, then beat with an electric mixer.
Add salt and red pepper.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until mixture is stiff.
Use a cookie press with different shapes for a more festive appearance. Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Biscuits will be yellow instead of brown.

title: pecan roll topping
directions: Put in bottom of pan with rolls on top.
I break off the dough, dip in melted butter, white sugar and cinnamon.

title: soft play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Cook on medium heat, stirring at all times until ball forms.
Knead dough until soft. Divide into separate portions and add food color, if desired. Store in airtight containers or Ziploc plastic bags.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit in bowl.
Sprinkle pudding over fruit and stir.
Add nuts, etc. and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place hulled and sliced strawberries in 9-inch cooked and cooled pie shell.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions; combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed and pepper.
Bring to a boil 5 minutes at simmering point.
Pack into 8 pint jars, filling to top and seal.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, oleo and eggs.
Blend well.
Add water, coffee, soda, vanilla and baking powder.
Blend in flour and beat well.
Stir in raisins.

title: delicious fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: quick easy casserole
directions: Drain the Veg-All and tuna.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and peel.
Mash and add remaining ingredients.
Put into buttered 1 1/2 quart casserole dish and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: tarragon shallot vinaigrette
directions: Whisk together vinegar, shallot, mustard, salt and pepper. Add oil in slow stream, whisking until emulsified.	Whisk in tarragon.
Delicious on a salad with thinly sliced fennel, red onion, and shaved parmesan. Enjoy!

title: italian quiche
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Spread over deep unbaked 9-inch pie crust or quiche pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and oregano and pour over pepperoni mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix flour and yeast together.
In separate bowl, mix egg and water and add to flour mixture.
Add beer and salt last.
Mix together.
Dip dry pieces of fish in batter, then deep fry until golden brown.

title: apricot-pineapple sherbet punch
directions: Combine juices in large punch bowl.
Spoon in sherbet and add ginger ale, stirring slightly.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
Yields 20 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook together.
Great for low calorie diet.

title: cheesy potato patties
directions: Beat together eggs, flour, onions, salt and baking powder. Stir in hash browns and cheese.
For each pancake, pour 1/2 cup batter into hot well-greased skillet or griddle.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.
Garnish with sour cream, spiced apples or apple sauce.
Makes about 6 pancakes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball.
Finish by rolling or patting with paprika, chili powder, Tony's seasoning.

title: crab stew
directions: Cube potatoes; cover with water.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: down-home pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth. Pour into butter greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean. Serve with whipped topping.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Spoon into a greased baking dish.
Mix crushed crackers with melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Press into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through (approximately 30 minutes).
Serve warm on rolls or bed of lettuce.
Great on a cool day!

title: golden ham glaze
directions: In small saucepan, combine apple juice concentrate, vinegar, mustard and pineapple.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.

title: homemade chili sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers, onions and celery, then add rest of ingredients and simmer many hours until thick.
Makes about 10 or 12 pints.

title: moist bread stuffing
directions: In large pot or skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add celery and onion; cook until tender (about 10 minutes). Stir in bread crumbs, seasonings and eggs.
This will stuff a 10 to 12-pound turkey or can be baked in a casserole dish along with turkey at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broiled coconut frosting
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients and spread over warm cake. Brown lightly under broiler.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Make yellow cake mix batter according to box directions.
Pour cake batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Top batter with rhubarb, sugar and cream.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: linda's chili
directions: Cook meat, onion and pepper together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Eat as chili or pour over baked potato.

title: chesapeake bay crab soup
directions: Cook all vegetables together in water, barely enough to cover, and let simmer 1 hour.
In another pot, boil crabs very gently 1/2 hour.
Remove from water and cut into small pieces, shells and all.
Put into vegetables along with liquid in which the crabs were cooked. Add crab meat and legs.
Simmer gently 1 hour.
Warm a little water in a saucepan. Work butter and flour in and add cream, stirring carefully. Stir this mixture into crab soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onions, green pepper and garlic in butter.
Blend in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly and vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Just before serving, add shrimp.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve gumbo over cooked rice.
May add Tabasco to gumbo for taste.

title: christine's pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions and celery separately.	Add salt and water to ground cukes and onions and let stand overnight.
Add celery.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to vegetable mixture.
Boil for 10 minutes or longer then can.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except for chips and dressing.
When ready to serve, add Catalina dressing and barbecue chips and toss.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil onion and broccoli in chicken broth until tender.
Add flour to milk; mix well.
Add butter and milk to broccoli mixture. Stir until thickened.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and shortening, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix first five ingredients and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread chili sauce as second layer.
Spread crab meat as third layer.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute large onion.
Mix together and heat, soup, Cheez Whiz and broth.
Layer chicken and Doritos twice, then add sauce on top.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Tear off foil for each person.
This is for one person.
Put onion mix in hamburger and sauce.
Take a steak and put on foil. Put sliced potato, sliced carrot and sliced onions.
Fold up foil. Cook in 350° to 400° oven.
All you need is a salad.

title: apple bread to die for
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to batter, mixing well.
Stir in flour.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Mix butter, brown sugar and cinnamon and drizzle.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack.

title: grandma's best mayonnaise chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together until well blended.
Mix dry into wet ingredients.
Pour into two 8-inch layer pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: heavenly chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites, vinegar, 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon and salt until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup of sugar, 1/2 tablespoon at a time, beating until very stiff.
Spread over bottom and sides of pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes, until golden.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix together. Bake in 350° oven in greased brownie pan, approximately 20 minutes or until just golden on top.
Cool at least 10 minutes, then cut.

title: mom's cauliflower salad
directions: Chop lettuce and put in dish. Next
layer cauliflower and spread with mayonnaise.
If bacon is desired add now. Cover with cheese. Stir before serving.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Blend sugar and salt into butter and chocolate mixture with electric mixer.
Slowly add milk, blending until smooth.
Return to stove and bring just to point of rolling boil.
Remove from heat immediately.
Store in 5-cup container.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut livers into chunks.
Wrap each bacon piece around a water chestnut and chunk of liver; secure with toothpick.

title: low-fat turkey cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Drain.
Brown turkey and onions. Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Put potatoes in a bowl and add turkey and onions.
Add soup and cheese mixture. Stir lightly.
Put in oven or microwave and heat until nice and hot.

title: mayonnaise chicken
directions: Combine mayonnaise with oregano (about 2 tablespoons oregano per 1 cup of mayonnaise).
Rub mixture on chicken and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Place in oven and bake additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Drain the peas. Put peas in a shaker jar.
Add remaining ingredients and shake well.
Tastes better if left in refrigerator for at least 2 days before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for about a month.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and lightly beaten eggs.
Add mixture of sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt, mustard and onion.
Stir in milk and butter.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: chicken dinner in a pot
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place chicken breasts in heavy pan. Peel and slice potatoes, cut 1/2-inch thick.
Place on top of chicken.
Add onion, beans and carrots.
Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour sherry over all; cover tightly.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: strawberry graham torte
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup of the sugar and oil.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into small strips and fry it.
Pour off grease. Dice onion into small pieces.
Warm the pork and beans in a kettle.
Add all ingredients; warm until hot.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dimple's pralines
directions: Cook
until
mixture
forms
a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and add 1 stick oleo, 2 cups whole pecans and 1 teaspoon
vanilla.	Beat
and
drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: grilled swordfish sicilian style(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: If using charcoal, light it in time for white ash to form before cooking.
If using an outdoor gas grill or the broiler, preheat for at least 15 minutes.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend, then add milk until smooth.
Season and cook a few minutes.
Add chicken and mix well.
Pour out to cool.
When cold, take large teaspoon and shape into balls.
Chill until firm, then roll in bread crumbs, then in 2 tablespoons milk and then in bread crumbs again.
Bake in hot lard.

title: phillip's cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add fruit.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add dry mix.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet cauliflower pickles
directions: Break cauliflower in florets, should be 2-quarts.
Cook in a small amount of unsalted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add cauliflower and simmer 2 minutes.
Pack in 6 hot pint jars and seal.
Process 5 minutes.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: On low speed, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix until blended.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Mash 1/2 cup berries; stir in by hand. Add rest of whole berries; stir.
Grease muffin tins and tops. Pile mixture high in muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 30 minutes.

title: nutty noodle
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Alternate layers of noodles, beef mixture, olives and cheese and large can of mushrooms. Repeat layers, ending with beef mixture.
Pour mushroom soup (diluted with milk or water) over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles and nuts over mixture.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: homemade kahlua brandy(portuguese)
directions: Combine water and sugar, then rest of the ingredients.
Let set for 20 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add blended dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut into bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients, beating eggs well and add melted butter or margarine.
Fold corn into mixture.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dietetic fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in well greased pan at 275° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs.
Add and stir in the sour cream and bananas.
Combine dry ingredients; add to batter and stir until smooth.
Fold in the nuts and craisins.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Heat pineapple and sugar; cool.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Add gelatin and other ingredients. Blend with mixer.
Add pecans, if desired.
Freeze.
Cut and serve frozen or take out 1 hour before serving.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Combine shortening, salt, butter and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Stir in eggs.
Combine yeast and 1 cup warm water in a 1-cup measuring cup.
Let stand five minutes. Stir into egg mixture.
Gradually add flour, stirring until blended.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Pinch off 1/3 of dough.
Cover and chill remaining dough up to 5 days, if desired. Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on a floured surface.
Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise at room temperature for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
About 1 1/2 dozen per portion.

title: round steak and onions
directions: Cut steak into 4 pieces.
On a plate, mix salt, pepper, marjoram and flour.
Dredge steak in flour mixture.
With the side of a plate, pound flour mixture into steaks, adding more of mixture until steaks are about doubled in diameter and about 1/4 inch thick.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drink 4 ounces every day.
This mixture is said to reduce cholesterol.
Add honey if arthritis is a problem, approximately 1/2 to 1 cup.

title: muscadine or grape cobbler
directions: Press the seeds out of enough hulls to make 4 cups.
Cover hulls with water and cook until tender.
Pour into deep dish pie shell and cover with top crust or lattice strips.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until brown.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Cook brownie mix according to instructions on box.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to instructions (omit the pie crust). Cut or crumble brownies after they have cooled.
Place evenly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate mousse over brownies. Crush candy bars and sprinkle over mousse.
Put a thick layer of Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tacos
directions: Cook ground meat until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Return to skillet and add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and cumin; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in casserole dish. Put bacon on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and push bacon down into beans; lay cheese on top.
Bake for 15 more minutes.
Cheese should be melted when beans are done.

title: never fail divinity
directions: In pan, cook the sugar, syrup, salt and water to firm ball. Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Pour half of cooked sugar over the egg whites.
Keep beating.
Put other half of syrup back on fire to cook to crack stage, then add to egg whites; keep beating.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls.

title: mexican cheese and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Add oleo to hot rice.
Add soup and Mexican corn to rice.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken wing sauce
directions: Put chicken wings in a 10 x 13 pan. Mix ingredients. Pour over wings. Bake 1 1/2 hours. Every 20 minutes, turn wings. Serve over rice.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in sauce and salt.
Cook until thick.
Drain noodles.
Place in noodle saucepan.
Add cream cheese, milk and garlic salt.
Stir until cheese melts and sauce thickens.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Spread meat mix over top.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: nannie's applesauce cake
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar; mix.
Sift flour and spices (saving a little flour to mix with raisins).
Add to first mixture.
Mix soda in applesauce and add to first mixture.
Mix raisins last. If too stiff, stir in a little more applesauce.
An 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan works nicely.
Bake in oven.
